<i>Clinton campaign's unleashing</i>

01:36.285 --> 01:38.215
<i>a new campaign ad today.</i>

01:38.217 --> 01:41.283
<i>NYPD still hasn't given a
motive for the killing, so...</i>

01:41.285 --> 01:44.016
<i>...immigrants, but with
election day closing in...</i>

01:44.018 --> 01:45.417
MICHAEL: Danny boy.

01:45.419 --> 01:47.252
The pipes,
the pipes, the pipes...

01:49.351 --> 01:50.782
- WOMAN: <i>Danny?</i>
- I was up all night.

01:50.784 --> 01:52.183
WOMAN: <i>Hello? Hello?</i>

01:52.185 --> 01:53.683
- Uh-huh.
- WOMAN: <i>What are you doing?</i>

01:53.685 --> 01:54.815
It's almost 7:00.

01:54.817 --> 01:56.851
(INDISTINCT CHATTER ON RADIO)

01:57.850 --> 01:59.949
- Got a showing at noon today.
- Yeah.

01:59.951 --> 02:01.216
- Did you ever get hold of her?
- MICHAEL: Uh-huh.

02:01.218 --> 02:02.916
- Morning.
- Hey, kiddo.

02:02.918 --> 02:05.215
Why did I get a license
if I can't get a car?

02:05.217 --> 02:06.915
School starts
next week, right?

02:06.917 --> 02:08.181
KAREN: Mmm-hmm.

02:08.184 --> 02:10.882
Syracuse application.
Early admission's due.

02:10.883 --> 02:13.052
I spoke to Chris Simpson
about a referral.

02:15.984 --> 02:18.016
Most of my friends
are going to State.

02:18.018 --> 02:22.215
What? Danny, you worked
your butt off for this.

02:22.217 --> 02:23.951
This is your next assignment.

02:26.784 --> 02:28.683
Okay, what chapter are you on?

02:28.685 --> 02:29.617
Halfway through five.

02:29.619 --> 02:33.083
The part where they almost
kill that kid.

02:33.085 --> 02:35.350
You know that I can
get through on my own now.

02:35.352 --> 02:36.983
We made it this far, kid.

02:36.985 --> 02:38.848
You wanna write
the book report, too?

02:38.850 --> 02:40.215
Couple thinks 350

02:40.217 --> 02:42.050
- buys the keys to their dream home.
- (CAR UNLOCKS)

02:42.052 --> 02:44.182
- Yeah.
- "Can you show it to us at midnight?"

02:44.184 --> 02:45.384
- Midnight?
- Midnight.

02:50.052 --> 02:51.782
KAREN: And the school
we saw yesterday, yes,

02:51.784 --> 02:53.684
- it was private, but it's worth it.
- MICHAEL: Uh-huh.

02:56.918 --> 02:58.683
Have you seen
these estimates for tuition?

02:58.685 --> 03:01.082
And that doesn't
include room and board.

03:01.084 --> 03:02.086
What?

03:05.885 --> 03:07.216
We'll find a way.
We always do.

03:07.218 --> 03:09.218
(INDISTINCT ANNOUNCEMENT
ON PA)

03:13.052 --> 03:14.282
- It's got to be.
- Okay.

03:14.284 --> 03:15.583
- Uh, Wednesday?
- Wednesday.

03:15.585 --> 03:18.249
Unless it's written on a piece
of paper that she can hand...

03:18.251 --> 03:20.816
- I listen. I listen.
- You don't! You don't! You...

03:20.818 --> 03:22.749
(KAREN SIGHS)

03:22.751 --> 03:25.050
- (LAUGHS)
- I will not forget the look on your...

03:25.052 --> 03:26.119
I'll try.

03:27.817 --> 03:29.918
- I love you.
- I sort of like you.

03:32.184 --> 03:34.314
(WIND HOWLING)

03:34.316 --> 03:35.684
(TRAIN HORN BLARING)

03:45.817 --> 03:46.951
- Hey.
- Hey.

03:52.118 --> 03:54.085
WOMAN: (ON PA) <i>Please watch
the gap between the train...</i>

03:56.252 --> 03:57.448
MAN: (ON PA)
<i>Now leaving Tarrytown.</i>

03:57.450 --> 03:59.352
(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

04:00.685 --> 04:02.152
(TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWING)

04:05.950 --> 04:08.183
18 grand a year?

04:08.185 --> 04:11.285
Sweetheart, it ain't MIT.
It's preschool.

04:13.251 --> 04:14.848
- WALT: What now?
- MICHAEL: <i>Wuthering Heights.</i>

04:14.850 --> 04:17.916
- Charlotte Bronte.
- Emily.

04:17.918 --> 04:19.415
- Emily.
- Yeah.

04:19.416 --> 04:21.618
- I would not forget that face.
- (WOMAN LAUGHS)

04:22.717 --> 04:24.381
I think
we locked eyes one time.

04:24.383 --> 04:25.985
- It was like, boom, you know?
- (CHUCKLES)

04:31.685 --> 04:34.150
You know,
my son's on me to retire.

04:34.152 --> 04:37.748
I don't know. Maybe.
Every day's a grind.

04:37.750 --> 04:39.849
Begins to feel
like a countdown.

04:39.851 --> 04:42.749
This way in the morning,
that way at night.

04:42.751 --> 04:44.683
And then one day
it's done with you.

04:44.685 --> 04:46.685
- What's that?
- Life.

04:53.851 --> 04:56.116
All right, see you
on the next go-round.

04:56.118 --> 04:57.986
Take it easy.

04:58.817 --> 05:00.952
(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

05:22.985 --> 05:25.916
My father died when he was 43.

05:25.918 --> 05:29.250
Left me, my mom, my brothers
with mountains of debt.

05:31.052 --> 05:31.984
Thank you.

05:31.986 --> 05:34.214
I moved here from Ireland
with nothing.

05:34.216 --> 05:36.248
Made a life for myself,
my family.

05:36.250 --> 05:38.951
That's the reason
I do what I do.

05:40.017 --> 05:42.214
To protect
young families like yours.

05:42.216 --> 05:43.883
I will tell you this.

05:43.885 --> 05:45.314
My wife Karen and I,

05:45.316 --> 05:47.848
we worked hard,
did everything right.

05:47.850 --> 05:49.848
401k, investments,

05:49.850 --> 05:52.149
my son's education fund.

05:52.151 --> 05:53.748
In 2008,

05:53.750 --> 05:55.082
(WHISTLES)

05:55.084 --> 05:57.949
we lost it all.
Second mortgage was due.

05:57.951 --> 06:02.082
We liquidated our assets,
cut every piece of fat

06:02.084 --> 06:04.851
while the banks
on Wall Street got rich.

06:06.418 --> 06:10.214
The one thing we didn't cut
was our life insurance policy.

06:10.216 --> 06:13.916
With the higher rate.
But I know you too well.

06:13.918 --> 06:16.049
Twenty may not even cut it.

06:16.051 --> 06:19.883
Hey, Jeanie, would you pull
Jared Carlson's LTC policy?

06:19.885 --> 06:21.116
Sure.

06:21.118 --> 06:23.314
I'll look over it and give you
a call later today, okay?

06:23.316 --> 06:24.782
Alex Murphy called,

06:24.784 --> 06:27.217
confirmed drinks
at Paddy O'Brien's on 44th.

06:27.950 --> 06:29.118
Thank you.

06:32.018 --> 06:34.149
You can always reach out
to Webber and Finch.

06:34.151 --> 06:35.214
- (KNOCK ON DOOR)
- Yes...

06:35.216 --> 06:36.915
Hey, Mike.
Can I talk to you a sec?

06:36.917 --> 06:38.783
- Sure, yeah.
- My office.

06:38.785 --> 06:39.952
John, listen,
I'm gonna have...

06:42.184 --> 06:46.119
Ten years. Just like that.

06:47.216 --> 06:49.248
Your severance package.

06:49.250 --> 06:51.149
Corporate is switching
from a financial buyout

06:51.151 --> 06:53.215
to a medical extension.

06:53.217 --> 06:55.749
You're giving me
insurance, Frank?

06:55.751 --> 06:57.182
Medical's covered
for your family.

06:57.184 --> 06:58.883
Unemployment should subsidize.

06:58.885 --> 07:01.384
Karen and me,
we're hand to mouth.

07:02.316 --> 07:04.281
You call HR anytime.

07:04.283 --> 07:05.515
They'll answer
any questions you have.

07:05.517 --> 07:10.083
I've got two mortgages,
a son who's going to college.

07:10.085 --> 07:12.318
I'm five years
from retirement.

07:13.918 --> 07:17.016
I'm 60 years of age, Frank.

07:17.018 --> 07:18.882
It isn't personal, Mike.

07:18.884 --> 07:20.448
Your salary, benefit package,

07:20.450 --> 07:22.416
it's too much
against your return.

07:22.418 --> 07:24.249
You work hard,
you play by the rules,

07:24.251 --> 07:26.682
you're a good soldier,
and you don't deserve it.

07:26.684 --> 07:29.818
But the reality is sometimes
soldiers end up casualties.

07:32.284 --> 07:34.217
(DISTORTED)

08:11.350 --> 08:12.818
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

08:17.885 --> 08:18.916
Hey.

08:18.918 --> 08:20.317
KAREN: <i>Hi, honey.
How's your day going?</i>

08:21.383 --> 08:23.916
Good. What's going on,
sweetheart?

08:23.918 --> 08:24.949
<i>I didn't wanna bother you,</i>

08:24.951 --> 08:27.684
<i>but did you happen
to go by the bank today?</i>

08:28.850 --> 08:31.282
No. I thought
we were gonna wait.

08:31.284 --> 08:35.182
<i>Yeah, until this week.
We talked about this.</i>

08:35.183 --> 08:36.816
<i>Danny has to register
for classes.</i>

08:36.818 --> 08:37.715
<i>If we don't get an extension</i>

08:37.717 --> 08:39.914
<i>on the mortgage,
neither check clears.</i>

08:39.917 --> 08:42.217
<i>I mailed the tuition check
this morning.</i>

08:43.116 --> 08:44.816
<i>Is everything okay?</i>

08:44.818 --> 08:47.315
Yeah, yeah. Just in the middle
of it, you know.

08:47.317 --> 08:48.381
Same old, same old.

08:48.383 --> 08:50.849
<i>Okay, honey.
I'll see you tonight.</i>

08:50.851 --> 08:52.318
Yep. Bye.

08:55.016 --> 08:57.214
- Sorry I'm late.
- Hey, hey. There he is.

08:57.216 --> 08:59.349
How you doing?
How long you been at it?

08:59.351 --> 09:02.715
Only since security
escorted me from my building.

09:02.717 --> 09:03.882
Cheers.

09:03.884 --> 09:05.017
- Oh, no.
- Mmm-hmm.

09:06.216 --> 09:08.918
- Hey, two more for him.
- (LAUGHS)

09:09.751 --> 09:11.118
So how did Karen take it?

09:13.050 --> 09:14.916
Ah...

09:14.918 --> 09:17.082
- You haven't told her?
- Mmm-mmm.

09:17.084 --> 09:18.348
What am I supposed to say?

09:18.350 --> 09:19.682
I don't know, man.

09:19.684 --> 09:21.882
That some asshole suit
just fired me.

09:21.884 --> 09:24.382
She doesn't know
how bad it is.

09:24.384 --> 09:26.915
We've got nothing
to fall back on.

09:26.917 --> 09:28.014
Ten years.

09:28.016 --> 09:30.416
You build a home,
a life, a career.

09:30.418 --> 09:32.848
And then one day
they sit you down.

09:32.850 --> 09:35.948
"It's been a good run.
Thanks for playing.

09:35.950 --> 09:37.749
"See you at the eulogy."

09:37.751 --> 09:38.816
You want proof
you're a good man,

09:38.818 --> 09:39.948
take a look at your family.

09:39.950 --> 09:42.716
- That's what matters.
- Yeah, yeah.

09:42.718 --> 09:45.619
You gave up the job for them.
Don't forget that.

09:47.450 --> 09:49.916
Those seven years
we were partners,

09:49.918 --> 09:51.218
you always had my back.

09:52.417 --> 09:54.084
So let someone else
have yours for once.

09:57.885 --> 09:58.951
All right.

10:00.017 --> 10:02.215
Well, you could have
ended up like me.

10:02.217 --> 10:04.948
Forty-five, divorced,
kids hate my guts.

10:04.950 --> 10:06.951
Wish I was 45 again.

10:07.818 --> 10:08.951
(DOOR OPENS)

10:11.383 --> 10:13.849
It's a good thing you got out.

10:13.851 --> 10:16.314
It ain't just cops being cops
anymore, you know?

10:16.316 --> 10:20.115
It's politics, favors,
choose a goddamn side.

10:20.117 --> 10:22.249
- Sergeant Hawthorne?
- No, Captain Hawthorne.

10:22.251 --> 10:24.018
- What?
- Yeah, he made captain.

10:25.217 --> 10:26.883
Guys like you and me, Mike,

10:26.885 --> 10:29.214
we work hard, we do it right,
it doesn't matter.

10:29.216 --> 10:30.848
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

10:30.850 --> 10:32.782
<i>A city planning official
commits suicide</i>

10:32.784 --> 10:35.048
<i>after the DA announces
an investigation</i>

10:35.050 --> 10:36.783
<i>amidst swirling accusations</i>

10:36.785 --> 10:38.415
<i>of illicit payoffs
for the approval...</i>

10:38.417 --> 10:40.048
It's a corrupt world,
my friend.

10:40.050 --> 10:41.282
No good being the little guy.

10:41.284 --> 10:43.082
He's coming over.

10:43.084 --> 10:44.151
Mmm.

10:45.851 --> 10:47.715
- Here we go.
- Michael.

10:47.717 --> 10:49.215
- David.
- Been a while.

10:49.217 --> 10:51.915
Yeah, yeah.
Captain David. Congrats.

10:51.917 --> 10:53.748
Well, I spend
more time in City Hall

10:53.750 --> 10:55.349
than I do on the job.

10:55.351 --> 10:57.950
- That goes with the stripes.
- Yeah. Yeah.

10:59.251 --> 11:01.985
- Still selling insurance?
- Yep.

11:04.383 --> 11:07.748
- Sorry to interrupt.
- No, no.

11:07.750 --> 11:09.048
Lieutenant, a word?

11:09.050 --> 11:12.248
Aw, Cap, I just pulled a 12-hour
back to back. Can it wait?

11:12.250 --> 11:13.947
Sure.

11:13.949 --> 11:15.048
Anyway, good to see you, Mike.

11:15.050 --> 11:16.915
Yeah, you, too, David.

11:16.917 --> 11:19.882
- Be careful with this one.
- Yeah, I will.

11:19.884 --> 11:21.181
(ALEX LAUGHS)

11:21.183 --> 11:23.381
- Ah... You prick.
- Shh.

11:23.383 --> 11:25.217
(MEN LAUGHING)

11:27.751 --> 11:30.982
Listen, the Michael I know,

11:30.984 --> 11:32.348
he doesn't hide things
from his wife,

11:32.350 --> 11:34.416
and he isn't too proud
to ask a friend for help.

11:34.418 --> 11:36.049
I'll be fine. I'll be fine.

11:36.051 --> 11:37.947
That's your
Irish pride talking.

11:37.949 --> 11:40.214
- You should know.
- I gotta go pick up my kid.

11:40.216 --> 11:41.348
Mmm.

11:41.350 --> 11:43.682
Don't you have
a train to catch?

11:43.684 --> 11:46.381
- Yes. Jim, what's the damage?
- No, no, no, I got it.

11:46.383 --> 11:48.315
Promise me that when you get
home, you'll tell Karen.

11:48.317 --> 11:50.181
What, that you finally
paid for something?

11:50.183 --> 11:51.216
What's the old Irish saying?

11:51.218 --> 11:52.947
If you wanna know
what God thinks about money,

11:52.949 --> 11:54.181
look at who he gives it to.

11:54.183 --> 11:55.382
Look at who
he gives it to. Yeah.

11:55.384 --> 11:57.318
I'll catch you.
Jim, I'll catch you.

12:14.316 --> 12:16.048
WOMAN: (ON PA)
<i>Boarding call for the 6:25</i>

12:16.050 --> 12:17.985
<i>Hudson North
to Poughkeepsie. Six...</i>

12:18.884 --> 12:20.381
Excuse me. Thank you.

12:20.383 --> 12:22.385
OFFICER: Sir, can I see
your bag, please?

12:24.151 --> 12:25.981
Ma'am, this way, please.

12:25.983 --> 12:27.349
TONY: Can you believe this?
They're doing bag checks

12:27.351 --> 12:29.049
at goddamn rush hour.

12:29.051 --> 12:30.752
OFFICER:
Step forward, ma'am. Sir.

12:33.017 --> 12:35.082
If something's ticking,
let it through.

12:35.084 --> 12:36.848
OFFICER:
Forward, sir. Open up.

12:36.850 --> 12:37.850
I can't do it.

12:41.083 --> 12:42.948
Hey, Mike, you wanna do me
a quick deal on some insurance

12:42.950 --> 12:44.914
before I have
a friggin' heart attack here?

12:44.916 --> 12:46.948
Sir, your bag, please.

12:46.950 --> 12:48.847
Thank you.

12:48.849 --> 12:51.184
WOMAN: (ON PA) <i>Suspicious or
unattended package, please...</i>

12:53.283 --> 12:55.182
MAN: Hey,
watch where you're going.

12:55.184 --> 12:56.416
WOMAN: (ON PA) <i>Safety
is everyone's responsibility.</i>

12:56.418 --> 12:58.751
<i>If you see something,
say something.</i>

13:05.116 --> 13:06.284
BOY: I want to.

13:09.383 --> 13:11.114
AUTOMATED VOICE: <i>Stand clear.</i>

13:11.116 --> 13:12.284
(DOORS BEEPING)

13:13.685 --> 13:15.352
My phone.

13:17.117 --> 13:18.818
Shit.

13:27.283 --> 13:29.249
MAN: Look, man,
I'm already on the train.

13:29.251 --> 13:30.948
If it's gonna happen at all,
it's gonna happen tonight.

13:30.950 --> 13:32.951
No more excuses.

13:34.917 --> 13:37.314
- Hey, Walt.
- You get me a name?

13:37.316 --> 13:38.415
What?

13:38.417 --> 13:40.148
Well, that woman's
staring at you

13:40.150 --> 13:42.150
like she knows
something we don't.

13:44.284 --> 13:45.950
I don't see anybody.

13:48.351 --> 13:49.848
WALT: Everything all right?

13:49.850 --> 13:52.748
Yeah. Yeah, yeah, yeah.
Tried in the next car?

13:52.750 --> 13:53.982
No, I've gotta take a leak.

13:53.984 --> 13:56.115
My prostate's bigger
than your head.

13:56.117 --> 13:58.352
(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

14:05.684 --> 14:07.385
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

14:12.050 --> 14:13.982
Look, Manny, I'm telling you,

14:13.984 --> 14:16.215
the lines are fine,
but there's no power.

14:16.217 --> 14:18.048
Have 'em fix it
when we get in, okay?

14:18.050 --> 14:19.914
- <i>Copy that.</i>
- JIMMY: What if I try this?

14:19.916 --> 14:21.149
(ELECTRICITY CRACKLING)

14:21.151 --> 14:24.682
- Jesus, Jimmy. Come on.
- Hey, I did nothing.

14:24.684 --> 14:27.714
Hey, Tarrytown.
AC's out in this coach.

14:27.716 --> 14:29.814
Get a seat up front
while you can.

14:29.816 --> 14:32.848
- You look worn out, Sam.
- Yeah. 32 years.

14:32.850 --> 14:35.082
If the train don't kill me,
the people will.

14:35.084 --> 14:37.382
- Tell me about it.
- Yeah.

14:37.384 --> 14:39.818
(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

14:43.116 --> 14:45.415
- Do it for me.
- Stop it. I don't want...

14:45.417 --> 14:48.682
- Take the bag.
- Let... Stop it. Get off.

14:48.684 --> 14:51.051
Now, that's exactly why
I never got married.

14:53.283 --> 14:54.950
Just... God.

15:02.684 --> 15:05.182
VINCE: ...JP Morgan and Chase
all over it. Open your eyes.

15:05.184 --> 15:07.718
I told you to buy low,
didn't I? What?

15:08.383 --> 15:10.448
Are you serious?

15:10.450 --> 15:11.747
I said, are you serious?

15:11.749 --> 15:13.015
This is a Gieves
& Hawkes suit.

15:13.017 --> 15:14.282
Does that mean
anything to you?

15:14.284 --> 15:15.781
Of course it doesn't.

15:15.783 --> 15:18.782
Yeah. If he's a piker,
get rid of him.

15:18.784 --> 15:20.148
Wipe him off the table.
Put him in the trash.

15:20.150 --> 15:21.349
Find someone
who can trade size.

15:21.351 --> 15:24.148
This gives me F.U. money.

15:24.150 --> 15:25.948
I caught big.

15:25.950 --> 15:27.782
You can't afford a suit,
you don't get in. I told him.

15:27.784 --> 15:29.014
Tickets, please.
Let me get your tickets.

15:29.016 --> 15:30.050
Thank you very much.

15:33.684 --> 15:35.416
Thank you. You got a ticket
there, young lady?

15:35.418 --> 15:38.282
You buy a ticket on the train,
I gotta charge you a penalty.

15:38.284 --> 15:40.349
VINCE: It sucks.
I know. Tell me about it.

15:40.351 --> 15:41.881
Bureaucrats.

15:41.883 --> 15:42.984
JIMMY: Tickets out, everybody.

15:45.317 --> 15:46.881
Thanks, Gordon.
Thank you very much.

15:46.883 --> 15:48.282
Knicks game. Knicks game.

15:48.284 --> 15:50.081
Hey, get your feet off
the seat there, sweetheart.

15:50.083 --> 15:51.281
You got a ticket?

15:51.283 --> 15:53.014
VINCE: It's a goddamn shame.

15:53.016 --> 15:54.915
Shut your mouth. Of course
I know what I'm talking about.

15:54.917 --> 15:56.348
How many years have I been
doing this? Tell me.

15:56.350 --> 15:58.215
Do you mind?

15:58.217 --> 16:00.982
I mind your 99-cent perfume.

16:00.984 --> 16:02.848
- JIMMY: Tickets, guys.
- No, now I'm talking to you.

16:02.850 --> 16:04.714
JIMMY: Thank you.

16:04.716 --> 16:07.218
Come on, come on. Bye-bye.

16:08.384 --> 16:11.049
Go ahead. Send it through.

16:11.051 --> 16:13.215
I'm looking
at the numbers now.

16:13.217 --> 16:15.348
SAM: (ON PA) <i>Now arriving
68th Street Station.</i>

16:15.350 --> 16:17.818
(INDISTINCT ANNOUNCEMENT
ON PA)

16:31.050 --> 16:32.948
(PA DINGS)

16:32.950 --> 16:35.981
SAM: (ON PA) <i>Now leaving
68th Street Station.</i>

16:35.983 --> 16:38.351
<i>Next stop,
86th Street Station.</i>

16:57.316 --> 16:59.315
JOANNA: Steinbeck, huh?

16:59.317 --> 17:01.015
Some say his greatest work

17:01.017 --> 17:02.651
was a letter
he wrote to his son.

17:04.450 --> 17:06.984
- Your book.
- Right.

17:08.184 --> 17:10.184
I beg your pardon.

17:12.317 --> 17:14.017
Thank you.

17:19.684 --> 17:21.814
It's my first time
on a commuter train.

17:21.816 --> 17:24.314
It's eclectic.

17:24.316 --> 17:28.182
- What about you?
- Every day. Last 10 years.

17:28.184 --> 17:29.315
Ten years?

17:29.317 --> 17:31.848
You must know
everyone on this train.

17:31.850 --> 17:35.947
The regular commuters,
I guess. Faces mostly.

17:35.949 --> 17:38.251
- I'm sorry. Have we met?
- No. I'm Joanna.

17:39.084 --> 17:41.085
- Michael.
- Michael.

17:44.351 --> 17:46.682
How long is it between stops?
Four minutes?

17:46.684 --> 17:48.847
Yeah, give or take.

17:48.849 --> 17:52.048
Four minutes.
On and off, on and off.

17:52.050 --> 17:54.249
It's so miscellaneous.

17:54.251 --> 17:57.382
- I'm bothering you, aren't I?
- No.

17:57.384 --> 17:59.352
I am.
You just wanna read your book.

17:59.950 --> 18:01.085
(SIGHS)

18:02.316 --> 18:06.049
It's... I'm married.

18:06.051 --> 18:07.682
Oh, I... Me, too.

18:07.684 --> 18:08.948
(CHUCKLES)

18:08.950 --> 18:10.715
- Sorry.
- I study human behavior.

18:10.717 --> 18:13.349
- It's an occupational hazard.
- Being married?

18:13.351 --> 18:15.847
- No, bothering people.
- Oh.

18:15.849 --> 18:17.850
I'm a conversationalist.

18:20.050 --> 18:23.049
So, in your job, you sit down,

18:23.051 --> 18:25.948
strike up a conversation.
Then what?

18:25.950 --> 18:29.382
Okay, let's say there are
100 people in this car.

18:29.384 --> 18:31.782
There are
16 personality types,

18:31.784 --> 18:33.381
as defined by psychology.

18:33.383 --> 18:35.714
And so I can assume
that there are about

18:35.716 --> 18:37.249
six people of each type,

18:37.251 --> 18:38.914
with varying
degrees of response

18:38.916 --> 18:41.081
to any particular situation.

18:41.083 --> 18:44.981
My job is to answer
one basic question.

18:44.983 --> 18:48.349
- What's that?
- What kind of person are you?

18:48.351 --> 18:51.349
Me? You should
probably ask my wife.

18:51.351 --> 18:52.884
(LAUGHS)

18:54.817 --> 18:57.215
- Let's do an experiment.
- Experiment?

18:57.217 --> 18:58.215
It's painless.

18:58.217 --> 18:59.718
It's just a simple
hypothetical question.

19:01.051 --> 19:02.818
Okay.

19:06.983 --> 19:11.683
What if I asked you
to do one little thing?

19:13.950 --> 19:18.015
It's something that you are
uniquely qualified to do.

19:18.017 --> 19:20.848
It's something
that's meaningless to you,

19:20.850 --> 19:24.318
but it could profoundly affect
an individual on this train.

19:25.683 --> 19:26.814
Would you do it?

19:26.816 --> 19:29.314
I'd want to know
what kind of thing.

19:29.316 --> 19:31.848
- Mmm-hmm. Does it matter?
- Well, I think it does.

19:31.850 --> 19:32.947
And you would never know

19:32.949 --> 19:34.214
the consequences
of what you did.

19:34.216 --> 19:36.084
Then why would I do it?

19:38.984 --> 19:40.951
Because there
would be a reward.

19:42.083 --> 19:43.150
A-ha.

19:45.116 --> 19:48.683
So, uh... What's the reward?

19:50.382 --> 19:51.783
(CHUCKLES)

19:54.950 --> 19:57.380
In the bathroom, carriage two,

19:57.382 --> 20:02.115
maybe there is a package.
It's hidden,

20:02.117 --> 20:08.049
and inside that package
is $25,000.

20:08.051 --> 20:11.818
That money is yours,
plus another 75 cash,

20:13.184 --> 20:15.351
if you do
this one little thing.

20:16.784 --> 20:18.217
I don't understand.

20:19.850 --> 20:22.681
Someone on this train
does not belong.

20:22.683 --> 20:26.218
All you have to do
is find them. That's it.

20:27.684 --> 20:29.714
This person is carrying a bag.

20:29.716 --> 20:31.048
You don't know
what it looks like.

20:31.050 --> 20:33.718
But inside that bag
is something they have stolen.

20:36.315 --> 20:38.714
This person goes
by the name of Prynne.

20:38.716 --> 20:40.815
It's not a real name.

20:40.817 --> 20:43.718
They will be on this train
until Cold Spring.

20:46.350 --> 20:48.982
You find them,
you find the bag,

20:48.984 --> 20:50.684
that $100,000 is yours.

20:51.216 --> 20:52.283
(CHUCKLES)

20:53.784 --> 20:56.215
Don't leave the train
before finding the bag.

20:56.217 --> 20:57.714
Don't tell anyone
about this offer.

20:57.716 --> 20:58.847
Wait a minute. Wait a minute.

20:58.849 --> 20:59.948
Simple.

20:59.950 --> 21:01.718
I thought
this was hypothetical.

21:02.816 --> 21:04.114
It's just one little thing.

21:04.116 --> 21:06.348
It shouldn't be too hard
for an ex-cop.

21:06.350 --> 21:07.848
- Wait.
- SAM: (ON PA) <i>Arriving at...</i>

21:07.850 --> 21:09.081
- How did you know...
- <i>...86th Street Station.</i>

21:09.083 --> 21:11.817
- Oh, that's me.
- You're being serious, right?

21:13.382 --> 21:15.747
You have until
the next stop to decide.

21:15.749 --> 21:17.717
What kind of person are you?

21:25.816 --> 21:26.950
(DOORS CLOSE)

21:29.716 --> 21:31.314
(PA DINGS)

21:31.316 --> 21:32.782
SAM: (ON PA) <i>Now leaving
86th Street Station.</i>

21:32.784 --> 21:33.784
What?

23:05.817 --> 23:06.951
You're kidding me.

23:09.249 --> 23:10.650
(LAUGHS)

23:34.817 --> 23:36.817
Tickets, anybody? Ticket?

23:39.182 --> 23:41.017
(WOMAN LAUGHING)

23:45.950 --> 23:47.950
(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

24:07.350 --> 24:08.447
Excuse me.

24:08.449 --> 24:09.714
You're gonna
wanna move on, pal.

24:09.716 --> 24:10.982
The AC's out in here.

24:10.984 --> 24:13.213
Actually, I was hoping
you could help me.

24:13.215 --> 24:15.448
I'm looking for someone.
A friend.

24:15.450 --> 24:17.049
Okay.

24:17.051 --> 24:18.848
They're going to Cold Spring,

24:18.850 --> 24:21.248
and I was wondering
if you keep track

24:21.250 --> 24:23.381
of where everyone
gets on and off the train.

24:23.383 --> 24:27.313
Yeah, I take pictures,
I hand out surveys, you know.

24:27.315 --> 24:29.049
- I didn't mean it like that.
- (LAUGHS)

24:29.051 --> 24:31.781
Dude, it's tickets
and zones, okay?

24:31.783 --> 24:32.915
They buy a ticket
for a station,

24:32.917 --> 24:36.650
I punch the zone stub
and put it on the seat. Boom.

24:38.216 --> 24:41.815
Is that just day riders or...

24:41.817 --> 24:43.081
You said you're looking
for your friend, right?

24:43.083 --> 24:44.113
Yeah.

24:44.115 --> 24:45.313
You don't know
what they look like?

24:45.315 --> 24:47.080
- (CHUCKLES)
- You're asking me questions

24:47.082 --> 24:50.080
about passengers,
about protocol?

24:50.082 --> 24:53.981
I know, it's stupid.
We only talked online.

24:53.983 --> 24:57.247
She said she'd be here.
Lives in Cold Spring.

24:57.249 --> 24:59.216
You're meeting an online date?

25:00.316 --> 25:02.117
On a metro train?

25:04.683 --> 25:08.083
Yeah, I can't help you, pal.
No one can.

25:09.716 --> 25:11.347
- Okay.
- All right.

25:11.349 --> 25:13.350
You take it easy. Good luck.

25:32.049 --> 25:33.982
(PA DINGS)

25:33.984 --> 25:36.815
SAM: (ON PA) <i>Now arriving
110th Street Station, folks.</i>

25:36.817 --> 25:38.217
(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

25:46.315 --> 25:47.950
You Michael?
Michael MacCauley?

25:48.716 --> 25:49.948
Yeah.

25:49.950 --> 25:51.214
You found
what you're looking for?

25:51.216 --> 25:52.951
What?

25:56.082 --> 25:57.850
Yo. Are we doing this?

25:59.083 --> 26:01.313
No. No, I can't.

26:01.315 --> 26:04.247
Yeah, they thought
you might say that.

26:04.249 --> 26:07.682
- Wait a minute. What is this?
- It's a warning.

26:07.684 --> 26:08.815
In case you haven't
figured it out yet,

26:08.817 --> 26:09.951
they're watching you.

26:12.983 --> 26:14.814
(PA DINGS)

26:14.816 --> 26:17.381
SAM: (ON PA) <i>Now leaving
110th Street Station.</i>

26:17.383 --> 26:19.817
<i>Next stop,
125th Street Station.</i>

26:46.817 --> 26:48.947
- Tony, can I use your phone?
- What?

26:48.949 --> 26:51.081
Your phone. Mine was stolen.
I have to make a call.

26:51.083 --> 26:54.114
It's an emergency.
Please. Please.

26:54.116 --> 26:56.980
Yeah, okay.
There's no service till 125th.

26:56.982 --> 26:58.347
Sometimes in the back,
if you're lucky.

26:58.349 --> 26:59.681
Thanks, Tony.

26:59.683 --> 27:01.083
Don't quit outta my game.

27:08.249 --> 27:10.380
WALT: You figure out
who she was?

27:10.382 --> 27:13.682
The woman we saw earlier
that was eyeballing you.

27:13.684 --> 27:14.781
Huh?

27:14.783 --> 27:16.347
I figured
that's where you went,

27:16.349 --> 27:17.617
looking for her.

27:19.315 --> 27:22.316
Hey, no judgment. I mean...

27:28.949 --> 27:30.848
Mind if I borrow
the sports section?

27:30.850 --> 27:34.114
- No. Yeah, sure. Here.
- Thanks.

27:34.116 --> 27:36.314
- The Yanks are playing the Sox.
- Uh-huh?

27:36.316 --> 27:39.083
Five wins to clinch.
I'm feeling very confident.

27:46.784 --> 27:47.947
You know, my boy,

27:47.949 --> 27:49.447
he won't let me
watch it on TV.

27:49.449 --> 27:53.682
He says it's bad
for my blood pressure.

27:53.684 --> 27:56.681
As if the Yanks winning would give
me a heart attack or something.

27:56.683 --> 27:58.217
Don't know why the kid
is so worried.

27:58.948 --> 28:00.080
(LAUGHS)

28:00.082 --> 28:03.213
Kid spends more time watching
me than he does at work.

28:03.215 --> 28:05.414
Yeah, and that is what I get

28:05.416 --> 28:08.214
for teaching the kid
to do the right thing.

28:08.216 --> 28:10.380
Listen, I'm gonna stop
by a bar and get a beer.

28:10.382 --> 28:14.350
- Why don't you come with me?
- (EXHALES) I can't.

28:18.684 --> 28:19.818
I gotta make a call.

28:30.948 --> 28:32.682
Come on, Karen, pick up.

28:32.684 --> 28:35.816
<i>The mobile number you are
trying to reach is unavailable.</i>

28:38.948 --> 28:41.114
- OFFICER: <i>2-3 Precinct.</i>
- Detective Murphy, please.

28:41.116 --> 28:43.347
<i>Please hold.</i>

28:43.349 --> 28:45.715
<i>He's not in. Can I transfer
you to his voice mail?</i>

28:45.717 --> 28:46.614
His cell, please.

28:46.616 --> 28:47.949
It's an emergency.
I'm a friend.

28:50.082 --> 28:51.781
Hey, Murph. It's Michael.

28:51.783 --> 28:55.316
Listen, I'm on the train
just before Harlem.

28:57.983 --> 28:59.748
I don't know
what the hell's happening.

28:59.750 --> 29:01.814
This woman
approached me out of nowhere.

29:01.816 --> 29:03.681
She wants me
to find a passenger

29:03.683 --> 29:05.681
carrying some kind of bag.

29:05.683 --> 29:08.181
Murph, I think I've...

29:08.183 --> 29:09.814
Just send someone to my house

29:09.816 --> 29:11.817
and call me back
at this number, okay?

29:18.349 --> 29:20.080
(PA DINGS)

29:20.082 --> 29:24.247
SAM: (ON PA) <i>Now arriving
125th Street Station, folks.</i>

29:24.249 --> 29:27.350
I'll see you
on the next go-round.

29:37.315 --> 29:39.747
<i>Now leaving
125th Street Station.</i>

29:39.749 --> 29:42.749
<i>Next stop, Yankee Stadium,
folks, Yankee Stadium.</i>

29:46.948 --> 29:48.117
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

29:49.215 --> 29:51.081
Murph? Hello?

29:51.083 --> 29:53.047
JOANNA: <i>You accepted
the offer, Michael,</i>

29:53.049 --> 29:55.080
<i>and then you broke the rules.</i>

29:55.082 --> 29:57.314
SAM: (ON PA) <i>Sorry, folks. We're
stopping due to a red signal.</i>

29:57.316 --> 29:59.747
<i>We should be on our way
in just a few minutes.</i>

29:59.749 --> 30:01.813
What the hell is this?

30:01.815 --> 30:05.946
JOANNA: <i>Look outside. Corner of
MLK and Lexington. Quickly, now.</i>

30:05.948 --> 30:06.949
<i>Southeast corner.</i>

30:16.684 --> 30:18.314
What do you want from me?

30:18.316 --> 30:21.380
<i>I want you to accept
responsibility.</i>

30:21.382 --> 30:23.682
<i>We all suffer
the burden of choice.</i>

30:23.684 --> 30:26.248
<i>No one forced you
to take that money.</i>

30:26.250 --> 30:27.250
<i>Do you see him?</i>

30:32.249 --> 30:34.816
<i>We can't have your friends
talking to the police.</i>

30:36.816 --> 30:39.351
- I didn't tell him anything.
- <i>We both know that's not true.</i>

30:40.815 --> 30:42.813
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

30:42.815 --> 30:44.749
- (TIRES SCREECHING)
- (CAR HORNS HONKING)

30:45.948 --> 30:46.949
Somebody get some help!

30:48.716 --> 30:51.214
Oh, my God.
What have you done?

30:51.216 --> 30:53.313
<i>You did this.
You made your choice.</i>

30:53.315 --> 30:55.947
<i>Find Prynne. Find the bag.</i>

30:55.949 --> 30:59.214
<i>Or there will be further
consequences.</i>

30:59.216 --> 31:01.746
- Did you see what happened?
- You listen to me. Listen.

31:01.748 --> 31:04.414
JOANNA: <i>No, you listen.
I can get to anyone anywhere.</i>

31:04.416 --> 31:06.347
<i>Your wife Karen,
your son Danny.</i>

31:06.349 --> 31:10.946
You touch my wife, my son,
I swear to God...

31:10.948 --> 31:12.914
<i>I asked you to do
one little thing.</i>

31:12.916 --> 31:15.080
<i>Don't make it
more complicated than that.</i>

31:15.082 --> 31:17.814
<i>Don't make me
hurt someone you love.</i>

31:17.816 --> 31:20.680
Wait, wait, wait.

31:20.682 --> 31:23.080
The day riders all have ticket
stubs in the back of their seats.

31:23.082 --> 31:24.713
I can narrow down
which passengers

31:24.715 --> 31:26.213
are going to Cold Spring.

31:26.215 --> 31:28.081
- <i>Now we're getting somewhere.</i>
- What's in the bag?

31:28.083 --> 31:29.348
What do I do when I find it?

31:29.350 --> 31:31.117
<i>Check your
right jacket pocket.</i>

31:34.082 --> 31:37.680
- <i>Do you know what that is?</i>
- It's a GPS tracker.

31:37.682 --> 31:39.946
<i>Clearly your time as a police
officer wasn't for nothing.</i>

31:39.948 --> 31:43.347
<i>Plant the device on the bag,
and it's all over.</i>

31:43.349 --> 31:44.347
<i>Dobbs Ferry Station,</i>

31:44.349 --> 31:46.947
<i>that's three stops,
arrives 7:00 p.m.</i>

31:46.949 --> 31:48.946
- <i>And, Michael?</i>
- What?

31:48.948 --> 31:50.949
<i>Give the gentleman
back his phone.</i>

32:56.216 --> 32:57.946
MICHAEL: Do you know
who's sitting here?

32:57.948 --> 32:59.050
Mmm-mmm.

33:07.216 --> 33:09.681
Excuse me. Does this train
go to Tenmile River?

33:09.683 --> 33:11.881
- MAN: Yeah.
- Ah, I thought that.

33:11.883 --> 33:12.950
Thank you.

33:14.216 --> 33:15.217
(CELL PHONE CHIMES)

33:46.848 --> 33:48.050
(SIGHS)

33:53.748 --> 33:56.380
SAM: (ON PA) <i>Now arriving
Yankee Stadium, folks.</i>

33:56.382 --> 33:57.882
<i>Yankee Stadium.</i>

34:13.949 --> 34:15.080
Um...

34:15.081 --> 34:17.112
Couldn't help
but overhear earlier.

34:17.114 --> 34:19.746
You're a broker, right?

34:19.748 --> 34:22.280
Can I help you with something?

34:22.282 --> 34:24.216
I haven't seen you
on the train before.

34:25.681 --> 34:26.750
There's a reason for that.

34:29.114 --> 34:31.813
You riding for business or...

34:31.815 --> 34:34.746
Well, I... My wife and I
are getting ready to retire,

34:34.748 --> 34:37.112
and we're looking
for a new broker.

34:37.114 --> 34:39.214
I work for one of the largest
investment banks in the world.

34:39.216 --> 34:40.414
Great. That's exactly...

34:40.416 --> 34:42.150
We don't represent
people like you.

34:45.083 --> 34:46.179
You're headed to Cold Spring.

34:46.181 --> 34:50.114
I figured maybe you were
seeing a client out there.

34:50.116 --> 34:51.750
What makes you think
I'm going to Cold Spring?

34:53.081 --> 34:54.681
- I don't know.
- What's your deal, man?

34:55.417 --> 34:56.679
Let me guess.

34:56.681 --> 34:59.147
The suit,
the shoes, the watch.

34:59.149 --> 35:00.580
(SCOFFS) You've probably
worked sales the last 20 years

35:00.582 --> 35:03.749
and now you wanna turn your nest egg
into a three-week timeshare in Maui.

35:07.448 --> 35:09.882
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

35:20.683 --> 35:22.681
Yeah.

35:22.683 --> 35:24.080
No, you got me
on a train to nowhere.

35:24.082 --> 35:26.147
Seriously, I never should
have left Goldman Sachs.

35:26.149 --> 35:27.746
Hey, Goldman Sachs.

35:27.748 --> 35:30.816
On behalf of the American
middle class, fuck you.

35:34.816 --> 35:37.080
Sorry, Ma. Go ahead.

35:37.082 --> 35:38.217
No, it was nothing.

35:47.815 --> 35:50.379
- Long day, huh, Sherri?
- Yeah.

35:50.381 --> 35:52.213
But you've been busy, huh,

35:52.215 --> 35:54.379
up and down
the aisle the whole time.

35:54.381 --> 35:56.681
Karen's been on at me
to get more exercise.

35:56.683 --> 35:58.913
It's either the train
or Pilates.

35:58.915 --> 36:00.080
(LAUGHS)

36:00.082 --> 36:03.680
- How is the family?
- Good. Good.

36:03.682 --> 36:05.946
Danny's headed off
to Syracuse.

36:05.948 --> 36:07.413
Wow. You must be really proud.

36:07.415 --> 36:09.813
Yeah. He's trying to decide

36:09.815 --> 36:11.746
between the dorms
or an apartment,

36:11.748 --> 36:13.880
the dorms or an apartment...

36:13.882 --> 36:15.013
(MICHAEL CLEARS THROAT)

36:15.015 --> 36:17.379
Excuse me. Hello?

36:17.381 --> 36:22.746
You go to Columbia, right?
T-shirt.

36:22.748 --> 36:26.749
Are you a photography student?
I noticed your camera case.

36:29.815 --> 36:31.817
I don't know... Um, I'm sorry.

36:36.083 --> 36:37.717
Millennials, huh?

36:44.250 --> 36:45.980
Excuse me.
Could you just wait?

36:45.982 --> 36:48.014
- <i>Now arriving Dobbs Ferry.</i>
- Hey.

36:48.016 --> 36:49.247
I only wanna talk.

36:49.249 --> 36:51.746
Oh, jeez!

36:51.748 --> 36:55.084
What are you doing?
Are you crazy?

36:55.849 --> 36:56.947
MICHAEL: What is this?

36:56.949 --> 36:58.813
Nothing. Can you just...
Stop it.

36:58.815 --> 36:59.680
Fake IDs?

36:59.682 --> 37:02.013
They're not mine,
I swear to God.

37:02.015 --> 37:03.081
They're my boyfriend's,

37:03.083 --> 37:04.680
and he asked me
if I could carry it

37:04.682 --> 37:06.682
because he would get caught.

37:08.349 --> 37:09.847
Are you a cop?

37:09.849 --> 37:11.214
No, I'm not a cop.

37:11.216 --> 37:13.214
But, listen,
if he really cared about you,

37:13.216 --> 37:15.816
he wouldn't ask you
to do something like this.

37:17.216 --> 37:18.846
- Yeah, okay.
- (PA DINGS)

37:18.848 --> 37:20.746
SAM: (ON PA)
<i>Now leaving Dobbs Ferry.</i>

37:20.748 --> 37:22.749
<i>Next stop, Tarrytown.</i>

37:29.416 --> 37:31.682
(EVA SPEAKING SPANISH)

37:47.748 --> 37:49.080
SAM: Are you sure?

37:49.082 --> 37:50.681
Maybe it's nothing.

37:50.683 --> 37:53.248
Look, they were all sitting
together, three of them.

37:53.250 --> 37:55.347
- Right.
- At 125th they split up,

37:55.349 --> 37:57.148
each to a different car.

37:57.150 --> 37:59.213
I don't know, it felt weird.

37:59.215 --> 38:01.148
I'm only authorized
to search a bag

38:01.150 --> 38:02.713
if it's been left behind.

38:02.715 --> 38:04.414
You know
I ride this line every day.

38:04.416 --> 38:06.347
Like I said,
maybe it's nothing,

38:06.349 --> 38:09.713
but "see something,
say something," right?

38:09.715 --> 38:12.016
- You point 'em out to me?
- Yeah.

38:16.348 --> 38:18.981
The woman there.

38:18.983 --> 38:20.813
The nurse.

38:20.815 --> 38:22.013
Man in the second car,

38:22.015 --> 38:24.014
African-American,
with a guitar.

38:24.016 --> 38:27.350
Another in the last car.
All going to Cold Spring.

38:51.015 --> 38:52.279
Excuse me, ma'am.

38:52.281 --> 38:55.680
I have to carry out
some random security checks,

38:55.682 --> 38:57.116
and I just need to take
a look in your bag.

38:57.682 --> 38:58.615
EVA: Why?

38:58.617 --> 38:59.748
I just need to take
a look in your bag.

38:59.750 --> 39:01.781
Hey, hey, hey! What do
you think you're doing?

39:01.783 --> 39:03.447
- It's a random security check.
- EVA: I know my rights.

39:03.449 --> 39:04.546
SAM: Get back to your books.

39:04.548 --> 39:07.713
I just need to take
a look in your bag, ma'am.

39:07.715 --> 39:11.080
EVA: Why me?
Seriously, why me? Why my bag?

39:11.082 --> 39:12.115
(EVA SPEAKING SPANISH)

39:12.117 --> 39:13.446
SAM: You're disturbing
everybody, ma'am.

39:13.448 --> 39:14.847
Please just keep it down.

39:14.849 --> 39:17.148
Now, please,
just open your bag.

39:17.150 --> 39:19.746
I asked you nicely, ma'am.

39:19.748 --> 39:21.781
- Just, please, open your bag.
- I'm a nurse. Come on.

39:21.783 --> 39:22.881
Sorry, sir.

39:22.883 --> 39:24.114
I help people.
I don't kill them.

39:24.116 --> 39:26.913
I just told you, ma'am,
it's a random security check.

39:26.915 --> 39:28.148
Do me a favor, will you?

39:28.150 --> 39:29.914
Just open your bag.
I'm sorry, sir.

39:29.916 --> 39:31.984
Just open up your bag,
and I'll be on my way.

39:39.115 --> 39:41.080
Got a visual, but I can't
get to anything yet.

39:41.082 --> 39:42.816
I just need a bit more time.

39:51.749 --> 39:53.680
(BOTH GRUNTING)

39:53.682 --> 39:55.279
- Who are you?
- Calm down.

39:55.281 --> 39:56.682
Why are you following me?

39:58.715 --> 40:00.446
Are you the reason
they're searching passengers?

40:00.448 --> 40:03.148
- Prynne?
- What did you say?

40:03.715 --> 40:04.850
(GROANS)

40:09.249 --> 40:11.817
(BOTH GRUNTING)

40:27.849 --> 40:30.683
Who are you? What do you know?

40:33.716 --> 40:35.212
What...

40:35.214 --> 40:36.180
Whatever you think
you're doing,

40:36.182 --> 40:39.215
you know what's good for you,
let it go.

40:42.948 --> 40:45.182
Hey, man, are you okay?

40:47.282 --> 40:48.817
Yeah.

40:51.883 --> 40:53.883
(PANTING)

40:55.281 --> 40:59.916
You see that? Scumbag.
Tried to steal my wallet.

41:13.249 --> 41:15.216
This train's freaking me out.

41:32.449 --> 41:34.383
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

41:37.382 --> 41:39.916
Hello? What?

41:42.082 --> 41:43.783
Who is this?

41:47.115 --> 41:48.817
All right.

41:54.682 --> 41:57.082
Mike, it's for you.
Some guy says he's a cop.

41:59.282 --> 42:01.780
You don't look so good.
Everything all right?

42:01.782 --> 42:03.782
Give me a minute, will you?

42:04.348 --> 42:06.380
- Murph.
- <i>Mike.</i>

42:06.382 --> 42:07.914
You sent someone to the house?

42:07.916 --> 42:10.280
<i>Tarrytown local.
They're on their way.</i>

42:10.282 --> 42:12.881
<i>What the hell's going on?</i>

42:12.883 --> 42:14.914
<i>Mike?</i>

42:14.916 --> 42:18.046
This woman sits across from
me, calls herself Joanna.

42:18.048 --> 42:21.914
She offers me 100 grand
to find someone on the train.

42:21.916 --> 42:26.280
- They want his bag.
- <i>100 grand? What kind of bag?</i>

42:26.282 --> 42:30.146
I don't know.
Look, it sounds crazy.

42:30.148 --> 42:31.979
They threatened
Karen and Danny.

42:31.981 --> 42:34.247
They killed a man, Murph,
pushed him into the street.

42:34.249 --> 42:38.979
<i>Jesus Christ. Uh... Okay.
You still on the train?</i>

42:38.981 --> 42:41.414
- Yeah.
- <i>All right, don't do anything.</i>

42:41.416 --> 42:44.079
<i>I'm gonna call a friend at
the transportation authority.</i>

42:44.081 --> 42:46.313
I found him, Murph.
I didn't have a choice.

42:46.315 --> 42:49.446
- <i>What did you do?</i>
- They gave me a GPS tracker.

42:49.448 --> 42:52.046
The kid's late 20s,
black duffle bag.

42:52.048 --> 42:54.280
A snake-head tattoo
on his neck.

42:54.282 --> 42:56.913
Goes by the name of Prynne.

42:56.915 --> 42:58.781
<i>Prynne?</i>

42:58.783 --> 43:00.783
<i>Did you take the money, Mike?</i>

43:03.416 --> 43:05.781
<i>You want my help
as a detective or as a friend?</i>

43:05.783 --> 43:08.680
<i>'Cause it's two very
different things.</i>

43:08.682 --> 43:10.747
What are you
not telling me, Murph?

43:10.749 --> 43:12.847
(SIGHS) <i>Two nights ago,</i>

43:12.849 --> 43:14.914
<i>a buddy of mine in the ninth
caught a suicide downtown,</i>

43:14.916 --> 43:17.347
<i>a staffer in the city
planning office.</i>

43:17.349 --> 43:19.680
<i>It's all over the news.</i>

43:19.682 --> 43:23.215
<i>Thing is, this kid was in deep
with the wrong kind of people.</i>

43:24.382 --> 43:26.713
<i>There's a witness
who saw two guys</i>

43:26.715 --> 43:28.682
<i>drop him 35 stories
out a window.</i>

43:30.148 --> 43:31.948
<i>Witness goes by Prynne.</i>

43:33.248 --> 43:35.012
And I identified him.

43:35.014 --> 43:38.013
Someone on this train's
gonna kill him. Jesus.

43:38.015 --> 43:39.713
I had an altercation
with the guy.

43:39.715 --> 43:41.213
I got a bag full of cash.

43:41.215 --> 43:43.216
I just lost my job.

43:44.282 --> 43:46.880
She's trying to set me up.

43:46.882 --> 43:48.313
<i>All right, this is
what you're gonna do.</i>

43:48.315 --> 43:50.649
<i>Next stop, get...</i> (DISTORTED)

43:52.448 --> 43:55.616
Murph? Hello? Murph?

43:58.848 --> 44:01.147
You done?

44:01.149 --> 44:03.814
Come on, man. What the
hell is wrong with you?

44:03.816 --> 44:05.912
Sorry, Tony. Thanks.

44:05.914 --> 44:08.717
Great. Thanks for using
my battery up, asshole.

44:15.349 --> 44:16.979
(INDISTINCT ANNOUNCEMENT
ON PA)

44:16.981 --> 44:18.946
Why are we meeting
a witness outside the city?

44:18.948 --> 44:19.983
It feels wrong.

44:21.882 --> 44:23.880
Twenty minutes.

44:23.882 --> 44:26.347
All right. I'm checking in
with Agent Foster.

44:26.349 --> 44:28.749
As long as the witness
gets off that train.

44:58.214 --> 44:59.682
Everything all right?

45:31.349 --> 45:33.115
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

45:53.282 --> 45:55.815
(GRUNTING)

45:59.182 --> 46:01.649
(CELL PHONE CONTINUES RINGING)

46:25.214 --> 46:27.349
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

46:41.149 --> 46:42.880
JOANNA:
<i>Look what you did, Michael.</i>

46:42.882 --> 46:43.949
<i>Another dead passenger.</i>

46:46.882 --> 46:48.346
This man was a federal agent.

46:48.348 --> 46:51.280
<i>Yes, but he's not Prynne.
You marked the wrong man.</i>

46:51.282 --> 46:53.680
- You killed him.
- <i>Whose fault is that?</i>

46:53.682 --> 46:56.047
- I didn't agree to this.
- <i>You tell yourself that.</i>

46:56.049 --> 46:57.446
<i>I know you think
you're a good man,</i>

46:57.448 --> 46:59.279
<i>but some part of you
was willing.</i>

46:59.281 --> 47:02.046
<i>Some part of you capable
of condemning a stranger</i>

47:02.048 --> 47:03.179
<i>to an unknown fate.</i>

47:03.181 --> 47:04.781
I'm done playing games.

47:10.814 --> 47:12.279
AUTOMATED VOICE: <i>The mobile
number you are trying to...</i>

47:12.281 --> 47:14.815
- Shit.
- <i>...reach is unavailable.</i>

47:17.981 --> 47:19.212
I wanna talk to my wife.

47:19.214 --> 47:20.813
JOANNA:
<i>Stay with me, Michael.</i>

47:20.815 --> 47:22.312
<i>You still have a job to do.</i>

47:22.314 --> 47:23.845
I will not do a goddamn thing

47:23.847 --> 47:26.912
until I know my wife
and my son are okay.

47:26.914 --> 47:28.916
<i>They're just leaving
the house now.</i>

47:31.714 --> 47:34.447
DANNY: <i>Mom, come on.
We're gonna be late.</i>

47:34.449 --> 47:36.779
KAREN: <i>Danny,
have you seen my ring?</i>

47:36.781 --> 47:39.048
<i>I swear I left it
on the bathroom counter.</i>

47:41.014 --> 47:42.414
DANNY: <i>Have you asked Dad?</i>

47:42.416 --> 47:44.945
KAREN: <i>He's not
picking up his phone as usual.</i>

47:44.947 --> 47:46.945
- (CAR DOOR UNLOCKS)
- (CAR APPROACHING)

47:46.947 --> 47:48.047
(BRAKES SCREECH)

47:48.049 --> 47:50.049
DANNY: <i>Mom, who is that?</i>

47:51.215 --> 47:54.749
KAREN: <i>Danny, get in the car.
Lock the door.</i>

47:56.416 --> 47:58.012
<i>Can I help you?</i>

47:58.014 --> 48:01.845
- MAN: <i>Are you Karen MacCauley?</i>
- KAREN: <i>Yes.</i>

48:01.847 --> 48:04.279
MAN: <i>I'm here because
of your husband.</i>

48:04.281 --> 48:06.212
KAREN: <i>I'm sorry. Do I know...</i>

48:06.214 --> 48:07.215
(CALL DISCONNECTS)

48:11.048 --> 48:14.112
JOANNA: <i>You have
a beautiful family, Michael.</i>

48:14.114 --> 48:16.280
SAM: (ON PA)
<i>Now arriving Tarrytown.</i>

48:16.282 --> 48:18.280
There are police
on their way right now.

48:18.282 --> 48:19.179
If your men try anything...

48:19.181 --> 48:20.314
<i>Yes, they were, Michael.
They were.</i>

48:20.316 --> 48:22.980
<i>Until you called too much
attention to yourself.</i>

48:22.982 --> 48:24.880
- What?
- <i>Look outside.</i>

48:24.882 --> 48:27.679
<i>Someone reported a dangerous
individual on the train.</i>

48:27.681 --> 48:31.113
<i>Now you're standing over
a corpse. Do the math.</i>

48:31.115 --> 48:32.246
What do you want me to do?

48:32.248 --> 48:35.349
<i>Don't leave the train
and don't get caught.</i>

49:02.681 --> 49:03.846
SAM: <i>I've been doing this
a long time.</i>

49:03.848 --> 49:05.447
I'm telling you,
he's a regular.

49:05.449 --> 49:06.680
I don't think he's dangerous.

49:06.682 --> 49:09.679
The guy claims he's looking
for someone onboard, right?

49:09.681 --> 49:11.446
He makes up
some bullshit story

49:11.448 --> 49:13.312
about suspicious bags,

49:13.314 --> 49:15.048
and then he gets into a fight.

49:16.416 --> 49:18.681
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATION)

49:30.049 --> 49:31.815
(GRUNTING)

49:39.315 --> 49:41.383
(POLICE RADIO CHATTER)

50:05.349 --> 50:06.946
SAM: (ON PA)
<i>Sorry for the delay, folks.</i>

50:06.948 --> 50:08.716
<i>We'll be on our way very soon.</i>

50:11.015 --> 50:12.746
OFFICER 1: Compartments
one and two all clear.

50:12.748 --> 50:14.280
- Call the captain.
- OFFICER 2: Yes, sir.

50:14.282 --> 50:16.880
Got two and three clear.
Three and four clear.

50:16.882 --> 50:19.079
OFFICER 3: Compartments
five and six clear.

50:19.081 --> 50:20.413
OFFICER 1: No, he's not here.

50:20.415 --> 50:22.049
OFFICER 4:
Okay, wrap it up, boys.

50:25.349 --> 50:27.082
(GRUNTING)

50:51.415 --> 50:52.813
(HYDRAULICS HISSING)

50:52.815 --> 50:53.882
(ENGINE REVVING)

51:17.081 --> 51:18.082
(GRUNTING)

51:36.815 --> 51:38.080
(GRUNTS)

51:38.082 --> 51:39.316
(GROANING)

52:18.248 --> 52:19.748
(PANTING)

52:22.747 --> 52:24.715
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

52:27.447 --> 52:29.948
(MUTTERING)

52:33.014 --> 52:34.279
JOANNA:
<i>That was impressive, Michael.</i>

52:34.281 --> 52:36.013
<i>I almost thought
you were gonna miss the train.</i>

52:36.015 --> 52:37.813
I wanna talk
to my wife and my son.

52:37.815 --> 52:38.879
I wanna know they're safe.

52:38.881 --> 52:41.046
<i>There are two more stops
before Cold Spring.</i>

52:41.048 --> 52:42.779
<i>Garrison Station
is your last chance,</i>

52:42.781 --> 52:44.946
<i>if you ever wanna
talk to them again.</i>

52:44.948 --> 52:47.812
I need more time.
There isn't enough to go on.

52:47.814 --> 52:49.446
<i>You've proven
yourself capable.</i>

52:49.448 --> 52:50.846
<i>Figure it out.</i>

52:50.848 --> 52:52.049
(CALL DISCONNECTS)

52:53.349 --> 52:54.983
(PANTING)

52:59.415 --> 53:01.882
(AIR-CONDITIONING BLOWING AIR)

53:09.814 --> 53:11.381
(AIR-CONDITIONING
POWERING DOWN)

53:12.681 --> 53:14.212
Hey, Manny, AC's cut out.

53:14.214 --> 53:15.813
I'm gonna check
the hub in three.

53:15.815 --> 53:17.046
- MANNY: <i>Copy that.</i>
- Hi. Excuse me.

53:17.048 --> 53:18.780
It's, like,
90 degrees in here.

53:18.782 --> 53:20.946
Yeah, working on it, ma'am.
Working on it.

53:20.948 --> 53:22.446
Tarrytown.
I thought you got off.

53:22.448 --> 53:23.949
Sam.

53:27.682 --> 53:29.946
You lucky son of a bitch.

53:29.948 --> 53:31.946
(TONY LAUGHS)

53:31.948 --> 53:35.079
My dad said it pays
to make new friends.

53:35.081 --> 53:37.082
- You wanna go again?
- JACKSON: Yep.

53:47.682 --> 53:49.312
<i>Ladies and gentlemen,
I'm sure you've noticed</i>

53:49.314 --> 53:52.680
<i>we've lost AC in all cars
except the last one.</i>

53:52.682 --> 53:54.179
<i>If you wanna move, please,</i>

53:54.181 --> 53:56.147
<i>remember your belongings.
Thank you.</i>

53:56.149 --> 53:57.346
Ladies and gentlemen,
I'm sure you've noticed

53:57.348 --> 54:00.745
we've entered the seventh
circle of hell. God damn it.

54:00.747 --> 54:03.115
(PASSENGERS GRUMBLING)

54:14.981 --> 54:17.348
(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

54:20.314 --> 54:23.349
Gonna be a hell of a ride
to Cold Spring.

54:35.182 --> 54:38.913
TONY: All right.
Two pairs. Queens. Fours.

54:38.915 --> 54:42.046
- Hey, Tony, deal me in?
- Your money to lose, pal.

54:42.048 --> 54:43.349
Come on in, Mike.

54:44.447 --> 54:47.179
I got 100 to my name.

54:47.181 --> 54:48.345
All right, Texas hold 'em.

54:48.347 --> 54:49.816
- Good?
- Sure.

54:50.947 --> 54:52.082
TONY: Okay. Gentlemen.

54:54.347 --> 54:56.049
Take a peek.

55:04.748 --> 55:07.680
- Doing all right there, pal?
- You don't wanna know.

55:07.682 --> 55:08.945
You should have got off
two stops ago.

55:08.947 --> 55:10.211
Ten years I ride this train.

55:10.213 --> 55:12.812
Maybe one time I wanna see
the end of the line.

55:12.814 --> 55:15.082
- (LAUGHS) Why?
- What about you, friend?

55:15.947 --> 55:17.780
What about me?

55:17.782 --> 55:19.949
Never seen you
on this train before.

55:20.882 --> 55:22.779
Well, I've never
seen you either.

55:22.781 --> 55:24.948
- You're not a regular.
- What is that to you?

55:27.682 --> 55:29.946
All right.

55:29.948 --> 55:31.813
I think your friend here's
got a problem with me.

55:31.815 --> 55:34.212
- Relax.
- Just making conversation.

55:34.214 --> 55:35.311
That's all.

55:35.313 --> 55:37.912
Well, if you wanna
say something,

55:37.914 --> 55:40.815
why don't you say it?

55:42.048 --> 55:45.279
It just occurred to me
that most of us,

55:45.281 --> 55:46.746
we ride this train every day.

55:46.748 --> 55:49.679
We nod. We say hello.

55:49.681 --> 55:52.012
But how much do we really
know about each other?

55:52.014 --> 55:55.211
What about you, Mike?
What do we know about you?

55:55.213 --> 55:56.812
MICHAEL: Fair enough.

55:56.814 --> 55:58.813
I got fired today.

55:58.815 --> 56:02.945
Yeah. Didn't have the guts
to tell my wife.

56:02.947 --> 56:05.812
Yeah. Have to go home,
look my son in the eye.

56:05.814 --> 56:07.413
What am I supposed to say?

56:07.415 --> 56:10.345
"I'm not the man
you thought I was"?

56:10.347 --> 56:12.815
What kind of father?
What kind of husband?

56:14.281 --> 56:18.946
60 years old.
What have I got left to offer?

56:18.948 --> 56:22.679
- That was extremely honest.
- And I thought my life sucked.

56:22.681 --> 56:24.080
Are we gonna play or what?

56:24.082 --> 56:26.148
TONY: Right.

56:27.248 --> 56:29.913
(GROANS) I'm out.

56:29.915 --> 56:33.146
So, I heard something
earlier today,

56:33.148 --> 56:35.146
- a hypothetical question.
- TONY: Uh-huh.

56:35.148 --> 56:36.779
What was the question?

56:36.781 --> 56:39.680
What if someone asked you
to do one little thing,

56:39.682 --> 56:41.178
something that's
meaningless to you,

56:41.180 --> 56:43.812
but would affect another
passenger on this train?

56:43.814 --> 56:46.780
Would you do it?

56:46.782 --> 56:48.278
I don't know.
What's in it for me?

56:48.280 --> 56:50.680
$100,000.

56:50.682 --> 56:51.679
Absolutely.

56:51.681 --> 56:53.046
MICHAEL: You don't
even know what it is.

56:53.048 --> 56:55.146
It doesn't matter. Come on.

56:55.148 --> 56:58.346
So what is
that one little thing?

56:58.348 --> 57:00.780
A passenger on this train
doesn't belong.

57:00.782 --> 57:01.946
They're carrying a bag,

57:01.948 --> 57:03.212
but you don't know
what it looks like.

57:03.214 --> 57:04.912
All you have to do

57:04.914 --> 57:07.311
is find them
before they get off.

57:07.313 --> 57:10.145
That's it?
It's not much to go on, Mike.

57:10.147 --> 57:11.211
Tell me about it.

57:11.213 --> 57:13.445
What happens
when you find 'em?

57:13.447 --> 57:16.083
They die. Hypothetically.

57:17.082 --> 57:19.345
So what would you do, Mike?

57:19.347 --> 57:22.211
I'd get all the people
left on the train in one car,

57:22.213 --> 57:24.746
propose that very scenario.

57:24.748 --> 57:25.946
TONY: No, no, no, no.

57:25.948 --> 57:27.214
I mean, would you
take the money?

57:30.414 --> 57:34.948
You know what? I already did.

57:37.347 --> 57:41.178
- You see, I count five.
- Five what?

57:41.180 --> 57:43.413
Five people left
that don't belong.

57:43.415 --> 57:45.946
Five people on this train
that I've never seen before.

57:45.948 --> 57:46.981
The lady right here.

57:48.948 --> 57:51.945
The young girl with the
pink hair at the window.

57:51.947 --> 57:54.012
Mr. Goldman Sachs over there.

57:54.014 --> 57:56.314
My friend with the guitar.

57:59.214 --> 58:00.215
And you.

58:04.881 --> 58:06.115
I'm Jackson.

58:10.415 --> 58:12.812
- You know what I would do?
- Tell me.

58:12.814 --> 58:15.013
I would pocket that 100 grand,

58:15.015 --> 58:17.145
find the guy,

58:17.147 --> 58:18.882
tell him to
take a different train.

58:20.148 --> 58:21.649
(CHUCKLES)

58:22.414 --> 58:23.948
TONY: All right.

58:26.314 --> 58:29.079
- All in.
- TONY: Whoa. Whoa.

58:29.081 --> 58:31.349
JACKSON: For real? All right.

58:37.682 --> 58:39.913
So, you never
answered the question.

58:39.915 --> 58:40.945
What question?

58:40.947 --> 58:42.345
What are you doing
on this train?

58:42.347 --> 58:44.680
JACKSON:
Maybe I'm like you.

58:44.682 --> 58:46.278
Maybe I wanna
see the end of the line.

58:46.280 --> 58:48.081
Wait a minute. Excuse me.

58:49.048 --> 58:50.946
JACKSON: I call.

58:50.948 --> 58:53.816
This is a monthly pass.
You're a regular commuter.

58:54.882 --> 58:57.949
Yeah. And I have a full house.

58:58.681 --> 59:00.211
Oh!

59:00.213 --> 59:02.615
- What do you have?
- That's it for me.

59:03.781 --> 59:05.281
I'm sorry.

59:15.948 --> 59:18.749
So what if I'm this guy
you're talking about?

59:19.681 --> 59:21.813
- Are you?
- If I was?

59:21.815 --> 59:24.011
Someone wants you dead.

59:24.013 --> 59:26.680
I can help you, but I need
to know what you know,

59:26.682 --> 59:28.212
why you're going
to Cold Spring,

59:28.214 --> 59:30.011
what's in that case.

59:30.013 --> 59:33.011
- It's just a guitar.
- Open it.

59:33.013 --> 59:35.145
You wanna help me?
Why should I trust you?

59:35.147 --> 59:36.215
Open the case.

59:54.081 --> 59:55.745
So what do we do now?

59:55.747 --> 59:59.312
You and I go to carriage one,
barricade ourselves inside.

59:59.314 --> 01:00:00.912
And then, what,
you gonna find this killer,

01:00:00.914 --> 01:00:02.046
take him down yourself?

01:00:02.048 --> 01:00:03.315
Gonna try.

01:00:04.448 --> 01:00:06.948
Obviously, I'm not Prynne.

01:00:09.881 --> 01:00:12.212
But you seem to have
figured that out already.

01:00:12.214 --> 01:00:13.680
That's a left-handed guitar.

01:00:13.682 --> 01:00:15.315
What's that got to do with it?

01:00:16.782 --> 01:00:18.682
Hey, man, are you okay?

01:00:21.882 --> 01:00:22.945
Yeah.

01:00:22.947 --> 01:00:24.379
The gun's in your right hand.

01:00:24.381 --> 01:00:27.146
(LAUGHING) Well, shit.

01:00:27.148 --> 01:00:29.082
I guess that's why
she chose you.

01:00:30.681 --> 01:00:33.014
Four passengers left.
Which one is it?

01:00:34.148 --> 01:00:36.079
I don't know.

01:00:36.081 --> 01:00:39.813
All you got to lose
and you don't know.

01:00:39.815 --> 01:00:41.279
You killed that agent.

01:00:41.281 --> 01:00:43.278
No, that's on you, man.

01:00:43.280 --> 01:00:45.911
How much is she paying you
to kill the witness?

01:00:45.913 --> 01:00:47.780
Same as you, I guess.

01:00:47.782 --> 01:00:50.079
But that's not really
how it works out, is it?

01:00:50.081 --> 01:00:53.082
No matter how much they pay,
you always end up owing more.

01:00:55.013 --> 01:00:58.081
Who's Prynne, Michael?
Tell me now.

01:00:59.181 --> 01:01:00.881
No.

01:01:02.348 --> 01:01:05.278
You have no idea
who you're up against.

01:01:05.280 --> 01:01:09.880
- Do you?
- Yes, Michael. I do.

01:01:10.348 --> 01:01:11.446
(COCKS GUN)

01:01:11.448 --> 01:01:14.948
- Drop it.
- Take it easy.

01:01:20.880 --> 01:01:22.348
Turn around.

01:01:23.447 --> 01:01:25.781
(BOTH GRUNTING)

01:02:05.347 --> 01:02:06.679
(GROANS)

01:02:06.681 --> 01:02:08.445
Who's Prynne?

01:02:08.447 --> 01:02:11.045
- I don't know.
- You're lying.

01:02:11.047 --> 01:02:13.214
(BOTH GRUNTING)

01:02:25.048 --> 01:02:26.115
(GROANS)

01:02:41.846 --> 01:02:44.681
- (GLASS SHATTERING)
- (WIND WHOOSHING)

01:02:47.281 --> 01:02:49.046
(GROANS)

01:02:49.048 --> 01:02:50.345
(PANTING)

01:02:50.347 --> 01:02:52.311
MICHAEL:
Don't be stupid. Stop.

01:02:52.313 --> 01:02:54.314
Not until Prynne is dead.

01:02:56.347 --> 01:02:58.348
MICHAEL:
I can't let you do that.

01:03:04.814 --> 01:03:07.147
(YELPING)

01:03:09.348 --> 01:03:11.349
(BOTH GRUNTING)

01:03:23.813 --> 01:03:25.481
(TRAIN HORN HONKING)

01:03:29.348 --> 01:03:30.982
(GROANING)

01:03:37.081 --> 01:03:39.048
(PANTING)

01:03:43.414 --> 01:03:45.814
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

01:03:50.414 --> 01:03:53.079
JOANNA: <i>You're out of time.
Who's Prynne?</i>

01:03:53.081 --> 01:03:55.815
It doesn't matter.
Your guy is dead.

01:03:57.681 --> 01:03:59.681
<i>You have the gun?</i>

01:04:01.813 --> 01:04:04.181
<i>Take it, Michael.
Take the weapon.</i>

01:04:06.913 --> 01:04:11.944
<i>Kill Prynne, retrieve the bag,
and your family lives.</i>

01:04:11.946 --> 01:04:15.345
- I am not gonna do this.
- <i>You can't have it both ways.</i>

01:04:15.347 --> 01:04:19.046
<i>You can save the witness
or your family.</i>

01:04:19.048 --> 01:04:21.744
<i>You know who Prynne is,
don't you?</i>

01:04:21.746 --> 01:04:23.780
<i>It's time to finish
what you started.</i>

01:04:27.147 --> 01:04:29.145
(PA DINGS)

01:04:29.147 --> 01:04:31.079
SAM: (ON PA)
<i>Now arriving Garrison, folks.</i>

01:04:31.081 --> 01:04:33.346
Hey, Mike, what happened
to the guy with the guitar?

01:04:33.348 --> 01:04:35.014
He got off.

01:04:38.181 --> 01:04:40.145
I better not be staying at
a bed and breakfast this time.

01:04:40.147 --> 01:04:41.747
Uh-uh. No way.

01:04:44.313 --> 01:04:46.047
(DOORS BEEPING)

01:04:47.747 --> 01:04:49.078
- (BEEPING STOPS)
- (PA DINGS)

01:04:49.080 --> 01:04:51.179
SAM: (ON PA)
<i>Next stop, Cold Spring.</i>

01:04:51.181 --> 01:04:53.616
<i>This train terminates
at Cold Spring.</i>

01:04:56.281 --> 01:04:57.648
(CELL PHONE CHIMES)

01:05:08.280 --> 01:05:09.814
(CELL PHONE CHIMES)

01:05:12.880 --> 01:05:16.047
- All that's left is you.
- What?

01:05:19.048 --> 01:05:21.978
Why are you going
to Cold Spring?

01:05:21.980 --> 01:05:24.348
- (CELL PHONE CHIMES)
- That's none of your business.

01:05:27.147 --> 01:05:29.279
- What's in the bag?
- My God.

01:05:29.281 --> 01:05:32.214
What is with you people
and my bag? Jeez.

01:05:32.947 --> 01:05:34.279
- Hey.
- Prynne?

01:05:34.281 --> 01:05:35.679
What are you doing?

01:05:35.681 --> 01:05:36.879
- Let go of me.
- I'm trying to help you.

01:05:36.881 --> 01:05:38.346
- Seriously, come on, do something.
- (CELL PHONE CHIMES)

01:05:38.348 --> 01:05:40.012
- Who is that?
- What's your problem?

01:05:40.014 --> 01:05:41.212
- Mike, you gotta let the lady go.
- (CELL PHONE CHIMES)

01:05:41.214 --> 01:05:42.445
You don't get it, do you?

01:05:42.447 --> 01:05:44.278
She wants you dead.
You witnessed a murder.

01:05:44.280 --> 01:05:45.945
You have something
that she wants,

01:05:45.947 --> 01:05:47.378
something she's
willing to kill for.

01:05:47.380 --> 01:05:49.944
- Okay, Mike, you gotta let her go. Let the lady go.
- (CELL PHONE CHIMES)

01:05:49.946 --> 01:05:51.045
- Mike.
- Hand me the phone.

01:05:51.047 --> 01:05:52.113
Mike, come on.

01:05:52.115 --> 01:05:53.948
Don't move. Don't move.
Stay in your seats.

01:05:57.280 --> 01:05:58.947
Please, hand me the phone.

01:06:11.380 --> 01:06:12.815
(CELL PHONE CHIMES)

01:06:19.214 --> 01:06:20.748
(CELL PHONE CHIMES)

01:06:22.447 --> 01:06:23.413
I... I don't...

01:06:23.415 --> 01:06:27.012
Look, I don't know
what your problem is,

01:06:27.014 --> 01:06:31.012
but I am not the person
you're looking for, okay?

01:06:31.014 --> 01:06:37.078
My... My boyfriend and I,
we had this huge fight

01:06:37.080 --> 01:06:41.082
because I wasn't sure about
staying here and us and...

01:06:42.681 --> 01:06:44.345
So when I finished my shift,

01:06:44.347 --> 01:06:46.947
I... I just didn't
wanna go home.

01:06:48.681 --> 01:06:51.614
Forgive me. Take it. Take it.

01:06:52.348 --> 01:06:53.815
I'm sorry.

01:06:55.813 --> 01:06:57.281
They're gonna kill my family.

01:06:58.680 --> 01:07:00.680
There's no one else.

01:07:02.081 --> 01:07:05.181
Six day riders.
Six ticket stubs.

01:07:06.213 --> 01:07:08.214
Six going to Cold Spring.

01:07:09.781 --> 01:07:14.781
Except... One got off
at Garrison.

01:07:17.080 --> 01:07:22.314
Goldman Sachs.
He... He was in the aisle.

01:07:24.213 --> 01:07:25.779
Bye-bye.

01:07:25.781 --> 01:07:27.282
He switched seats.

01:07:39.314 --> 01:07:42.048
(MUSIC PLAYING ON HEADPHONES)

01:07:50.314 --> 01:07:51.815
Prynne.

01:07:53.080 --> 01:07:55.880
Hester Prynne.
<i>The Scarlet Letter.</i> Of course.

01:07:57.947 --> 01:07:59.615
You bought the ticket
to Cold Spring.

01:08:02.081 --> 01:08:04.878
End of the line.
Cold Spring coming up.

01:08:04.880 --> 01:08:06.680
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

01:08:07.680 --> 01:08:09.413
JOANNA: <i>Is it done?</i>

01:08:09.415 --> 01:08:11.278
- <i>Is it done?</i>
- I will not do this.

01:08:11.280 --> 01:08:12.744
<i>I thought
I had you figured out.</i>

01:08:12.746 --> 01:08:13.815
<i>I really did.</i>

01:08:15.947 --> 01:08:17.111
Manny?

01:08:17.113 --> 01:08:18.812
<i>After all of this, you would
choose the life of a stranger</i>

01:08:18.814 --> 01:08:20.211
<i>over your own family?</i>

01:08:20.212 --> 01:08:22.212
<i>You must think
you're some kind of a hero.</i>

01:08:22.214 --> 01:08:23.679
I won't do this.

01:08:23.680 --> 01:08:25.145
I won't do it.
I will not do this.

01:08:25.148 --> 01:08:27.345
Manny, Manny,
we have a hostage situation.

01:08:27.348 --> 01:08:29.312
MANNY: <i>Calling dispatch.</i>

01:08:29.314 --> 01:08:31.412
JOANNA: <i>This is your
last chance, Michael.</i>

01:08:31.413 --> 01:08:32.745
- <i>Do it.</i>
- No.

01:08:32.747 --> 01:08:34.011
<i>Prynne has evidence</i>

01:08:34.014 --> 01:08:35.345
- <i>of a conspiracy.</i>
- That doesn't matter.

01:08:35.348 --> 01:08:37.812
<i>The people I work for,
they will do anything</i>

01:08:37.814 --> 01:08:39.011
- <i>to protect themselves.</i>
- What?

01:08:39.014 --> 01:08:40.212
<i>These are
very powerful people.</i>

01:08:40.214 --> 01:08:41.444
<i>They will do
whatever it takes.</i>

01:08:41.446 --> 01:08:42.644
They? Who?
Who are you talking about?

01:08:42.645 --> 01:08:45.212
<i>Even kill you, your family.
Everyone on that train.</i>

01:08:45.214 --> 01:08:46.444
- <i>Do you understand?</i>
- Who's they?

01:08:46.447 --> 01:08:48.877
<i>You have made your choice.</i>

01:08:48.880 --> 01:08:50.679
Joanna, who are
you working for?

01:08:50.680 --> 01:08:52.182
- <i>Now everyone dies.</i>
- (CALL DISCONNECTS)

01:08:54.214 --> 01:08:55.215
Hel...

01:08:58.180 --> 01:08:59.411
MANNY: <i>Dispatch
is contacting the police.</i>

01:08:59.412 --> 01:09:00.812
Stop the train.

01:09:00.814 --> 01:09:02.078
Copy that.

01:09:02.081 --> 01:09:03.246
(ALL YELP)

01:09:03.247 --> 01:09:06.212
You want to live, you stop
this goddamn train now.

01:09:06.214 --> 01:09:08.411
Pull the brake. Now.

01:09:08.412 --> 01:09:11.947
All right.
Now, everyone, hang on.

01:09:18.680 --> 01:09:20.779
(ALL SCREAMING)

01:09:22.080 --> 01:09:24.679
Yeah, thanks.

01:09:24.680 --> 01:09:26.679
Train's less than
a minute away.

01:09:26.680 --> 01:09:27.879
Marshal Service
is ready for us.

01:09:27.881 --> 01:09:29.078
Take the statement
at the safe house.

01:09:29.081 --> 01:09:31.211
No screwing around.

01:09:31.212 --> 01:09:33.314
- Why is it not stopping?
- I don't know.

01:09:45.046 --> 01:09:47.279
MICHAEL: Sam, I swear,
I had nothing to do with this.

01:09:47.281 --> 01:09:48.911
- Manny.
- Oh, man, that's not good.

01:09:48.912 --> 01:09:50.281
MICHAEL: Oh, my God.

01:09:51.913 --> 01:09:56.178
Help me get this open.
It's jammed. Come on.

01:09:56.180 --> 01:09:58.248
(BOTH GRUNTING)

01:10:07.881 --> 01:10:10.345
SAM: The engineer's dead.
Cab door's jammed.

01:10:10.347 --> 01:10:12.811
I can't access
the control panel.

01:10:12.813 --> 01:10:14.679
Dispatch, do you copy?

01:10:14.681 --> 01:10:16.179
The brakes have malfunctioned.

01:10:16.181 --> 01:10:18.348
There's no way
to stop the train.

01:10:19.681 --> 01:10:20.812
You what?

01:10:20.814 --> 01:10:23.046
DISPATCH: <i>We'll have
to clear the tracks.</i>

01:10:23.048 --> 01:10:24.211
SAM: Roger.

01:10:24.213 --> 01:10:25.779
Dispatch is gonna
clear the tracks.

01:10:25.781 --> 01:10:26.712
What?

01:10:26.714 --> 01:10:29.278
SAM: There's a curve
just before Beacon.

01:10:29.280 --> 01:10:31.079
Now, we hit it
at 70 miles an hour,

01:10:31.081 --> 01:10:33.945
we're gonna derail for sure.

01:10:33.947 --> 01:10:35.945
All the passengers
are in the last car.

01:10:35.947 --> 01:10:39.148
- Can we detach it?
- We have to try. Come on.

01:10:41.814 --> 01:10:43.445
We gotta unhook the couplers.

01:10:43.447 --> 01:10:45.744
There's a coupler
safety latch.

01:10:45.746 --> 01:10:48.082
It can only be released
from underneath the car.

01:10:51.346 --> 01:10:53.345
Someone will have to pull
the knuckle pin,

01:10:53.347 --> 01:10:56.915
and one of us will have to go
down and release the latch.

01:11:00.346 --> 01:11:02.245
No. No friggin' way.
I'm not going down there.

01:11:02.247 --> 01:11:03.311
It's just outside...

01:11:03.313 --> 01:11:04.812
I don't care. Shut up.
I'm not going down there.

01:11:04.814 --> 01:11:06.278
Just outside
and down the ladder.

01:11:06.280 --> 01:11:08.444
- I'll do it.
- Yeah, you do it.

01:11:08.446 --> 01:11:09.911
Look, you go
tell the passengers

01:11:09.913 --> 01:11:11.278
to brace themselves.

01:11:11.280 --> 01:11:12.180
I'll do that.

01:11:15.680 --> 01:11:18.277
We got about two minutes.
You make them count.

01:11:18.279 --> 01:11:21.011
Stay calm.
Stay calm, okay? Stay calm.

01:11:21.013 --> 01:11:23.344
- Remain calm.
- Why?

01:11:23.346 --> 01:11:24.744
I don't have time
to argue with you, lady.

01:11:24.746 --> 01:11:26.145
Sit down. Take your seats.

01:11:26.147 --> 01:11:29.014
- Everyone, sit down. Sit down.
- I am sitting down.

01:11:30.881 --> 01:11:32.314
(SAM GRUNTING)

01:11:46.947 --> 01:11:48.948
(MICHAEL GRUNTING)

01:12:02.413 --> 01:12:04.914
(BOTH CONTINUE GRUNTING)

01:12:14.312 --> 01:12:16.380
(CONTINUES GRUNTING)

01:12:27.347 --> 01:12:28.681
Yeah!

01:12:30.781 --> 01:12:32.313
(GRUNTING)

01:12:39.346 --> 01:12:41.679
(PASSENGERS YELP)

01:12:41.681 --> 01:12:43.681
SAM: The chain is caught.

01:12:56.681 --> 01:12:58.748
You need more leverage.
I'll get the ax.

01:13:13.080 --> 01:13:14.344
Between the train
and the people,

01:13:14.346 --> 01:13:16.680
I always knew
it would be the train.

01:13:32.212 --> 01:13:33.947
(BOTH GRUNTING)

01:13:46.846 --> 01:13:48.313
(BOTH GRUNTING)

01:13:51.447 --> 01:13:52.982
(GROANS)

01:13:58.048 --> 01:14:00.281
(ALL SCREAMING)

01:14:11.379 --> 01:14:12.814
(GRUNTS)

01:14:13.913 --> 01:14:15.748
(PASSENGERS SCREAMING)

01:14:57.680 --> 01:14:59.912
(PANICKED CHATTERING)

01:14:59.914 --> 01:15:02.145
TONY: All right. I'm okay.
You all right? Come on.

01:15:02.147 --> 01:15:04.412
- MAN 1: Get that door open.
- Everyone okay?

01:15:04.414 --> 01:15:06.945
- WOMAN: We gotta get out.
- MAN 2: Open the door.

01:15:06.947 --> 01:15:09.310
Stay calm.
Don't get off the train.

01:15:09.312 --> 01:15:11.011
Please, listen.

01:15:11.013 --> 01:15:12.348
- MAN 1: Get the door open.
- MAN 3: We gotta get out.

01:15:14.146 --> 01:15:16.177
(ALL SCREAM)

01:15:16.179 --> 01:15:19.077
Jackson, close the door.
This isn't over yet.

01:15:19.079 --> 01:15:22.144
We're still in danger.
Everyone grab a newspaper.

01:15:22.146 --> 01:15:25.412
Cover the windows.
Use water, soda, anything.

01:15:25.414 --> 01:15:26.811
Mike, this is crazy.

01:15:26.813 --> 01:15:29.614
Come on, get some water.
Cover the windows.

01:15:42.413 --> 01:15:44.744
- Why are we doing this, Mike?
- MICHAEL: Just do it.

01:15:44.746 --> 01:15:46.210
We don't know who's out there.

01:15:46.212 --> 01:15:47.878
Who's watching.
They tried to kill us all.

01:15:47.880 --> 01:15:48.980
- You all right?
- EVA: Yeah.

01:15:54.212 --> 01:15:57.177
I know you're all scared,
but I need your help.

01:15:57.179 --> 01:15:59.277
None of you
can leave, not yet.

01:15:59.279 --> 01:16:02.679
Not until I know
everyone's safe.

01:16:02.681 --> 01:16:05.811
They murdered innocent people.
They derailed the train.

01:16:05.813 --> 01:16:08.880
They did this.
All to find a witness.

01:16:11.347 --> 01:16:13.348
Something she has
that they want.

01:16:15.813 --> 01:16:16.943
They said
if I didn't kill you,

01:16:16.945 --> 01:16:19.110
they would kill
my wife, my son.

01:16:19.112 --> 01:16:20.045
But I would never.

01:16:20.047 --> 01:16:22.678
I would never do
what these people want.

01:16:22.680 --> 01:16:24.278
I need your help.

01:16:24.280 --> 01:16:26.146
I need to know
why they want you dead.

01:16:32.347 --> 01:16:35.077
- What's your name?
- Sofia.

01:16:35.079 --> 01:16:36.614
Sofia.

01:16:38.047 --> 01:16:40.815
It's okay. Come here.

01:16:49.313 --> 01:16:51.946
I'm not going to let them
hurt you, okay?

01:16:53.046 --> 01:16:54.680
Can you show me
what's in your bag?

01:17:08.046 --> 01:17:10.047
This? This is what they want?

01:17:12.313 --> 01:17:13.679
Do you know why?

01:17:13.681 --> 01:17:16.044
Because of Enrique.

01:17:16.046 --> 01:17:17.310
It was his.

01:17:17.312 --> 01:17:20.277
The guy who threw himself
off the 35th floor?

01:17:20.279 --> 01:17:22.679
Ricky didn't kill himself.

01:17:22.681 --> 01:17:24.181
You were there when he died?

01:17:28.212 --> 01:17:30.213
It's okay. Tell me.

01:17:31.813 --> 01:17:33.814
Tell me what you saw.

01:17:36.681 --> 01:17:39.779
Ricky was a city planner,

01:17:39.781 --> 01:17:42.944
and some nights
he would have to work late,

01:17:42.946 --> 01:17:46.910
so I would go to his office
to finish my homework.

01:17:46.912 --> 01:17:49.412
I was waiting
for Ricky by the elevator

01:17:49.414 --> 01:17:52.678
when these two men show up.

01:17:52.680 --> 01:17:54.943
I didn't see their faces,

01:17:54.945 --> 01:17:56.946
but they were
looking for Ricky.

01:17:59.012 --> 01:18:02.146
I hid 'cause I didn't wanna
get him in trouble.

01:18:04.180 --> 01:18:06.180
But they wanted
something from him.

01:18:07.879 --> 01:18:12.144
Then all of them
start yelling,

01:18:12.146 --> 01:18:14.344
and I hear this noise.

01:18:14.346 --> 01:18:17.444
They were hurting him.
I could hear him screaming.

01:18:17.446 --> 01:18:19.311
And he tells them
that he doesn't have it,

01:18:19.313 --> 01:18:21.045
that it's back at his place.

01:18:21.047 --> 01:18:23.344
- You took it.
- Of course I took it.

01:18:23.346 --> 01:18:25.815
I wanted to help.

01:18:28.812 --> 01:18:33.310
And then I look through the
doorway and I see this guy.

01:18:33.312 --> 01:18:36.344
He's holding Ricky,
and he hits him,

01:18:36.346 --> 01:18:39.681
and he says something
about being noble.

01:18:40.279 --> 01:18:41.411
Noble?

01:18:41.413 --> 01:18:43.778
He says that doing the right
thing will get you killed,

01:18:43.780 --> 01:18:46.780
and that there's no such thing
as being noble.

01:18:47.312 --> 01:18:49.014
And then,

01:18:50.781 --> 01:18:52.281
they just...

01:18:59.080 --> 01:19:01.211
I didn't know what to do.

01:19:01.213 --> 01:19:02.344
(SNIFFLING)

01:19:02.346 --> 01:19:03.678
I know.

01:19:03.680 --> 01:19:06.077
I just took it and I ran.

01:19:06.079 --> 01:19:08.078
Why didn't you
call the police?

01:19:08.080 --> 01:19:09.214
I couldn't call the police.

01:19:10.681 --> 01:19:12.947
The men
who killed him were cops.

01:19:15.279 --> 01:19:18.011
Oh, my God.

01:19:18.013 --> 01:19:20.914
And the next day I just...
I went to a friend's,

01:19:22.013 --> 01:19:24.144
and she knew
someone in the FBI.

01:19:24.146 --> 01:19:25.944
This guy, Agent Garcia,

01:19:25.946 --> 01:19:28.178
he says that
this drive is evidence,

01:19:28.180 --> 01:19:29.910
and that I'm a witness.

01:19:29.912 --> 01:19:32.278
He says it's not safe for me
in the city anymore,

01:19:32.280 --> 01:19:34.344
tells me to catch the 6:25

01:19:34.346 --> 01:19:36.814
to Cold Spring,
and they'll protect me.

01:19:38.212 --> 01:19:41.679
- You told no one else?
- No.

01:19:41.681 --> 01:19:45.081
Your friend trusts
this Agent Garcia, yeah?

01:19:46.779 --> 01:19:48.080
I don't know.

01:19:49.945 --> 01:19:53.743
Someone out there
wants you to disappear.

01:19:53.745 --> 01:19:57.813
And if it's not him... Who?

01:19:58.347 --> 01:20:00.846
(SIRENS WAILING)

01:20:11.745 --> 01:20:13.314
Oh, my God.

01:20:16.446 --> 01:20:18.680
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

01:20:25.414 --> 01:20:26.811
OFFICER: Go, go, go.
Move, move, move.

01:20:26.813 --> 01:20:27.814
What the hell?

01:20:44.446 --> 01:20:45.648
<i>MacCauley.</i>

01:20:49.680 --> 01:20:51.778
<i>This is Captain
David Hawthorne.</i>

01:20:51.780 --> 01:20:53.045
<i>I'm in command.</i>

01:20:53.047 --> 01:20:56.046
Entrance clear.
Let's go, go, go, go.

01:20:57.746 --> 01:20:59.344
HAWTHORNE:
<i>We have the train surrounded.</i>

01:20:59.346 --> 01:21:01.213
<i>There is nowhere
for you to go.</i>

01:21:04.679 --> 01:21:06.278
<i>Throw out your weapon.</i>

01:21:06.280 --> 01:21:07.811
<i>My men will come aboard.</i>

01:21:07.813 --> 01:21:10.211
<i>They will escort
the hostages to safety.</i>

01:21:10.213 --> 01:21:13.810
- It's okay. Don't be alarmed.
- <i>You will not be harmed.</i>

01:21:13.812 --> 01:21:15.010
This is
normal police procedure.

01:21:15.012 --> 01:21:17.944
It's okay.
You will all be safe.

01:21:17.946 --> 01:21:19.946
<i>No one will be harmed.</i>

01:21:32.379 --> 01:21:35.210
(SIRENS WAILING)

01:21:35.212 --> 01:21:37.213
TONY: Jesus, there's
a friggin' army out there.

01:21:43.180 --> 01:21:46.345
HAWTHORNE:
Agent Garcia, come to me.

01:21:46.347 --> 01:21:49.145
I need tactical staged
and ready to breach, okay?

01:21:49.147 --> 01:21:51.080
- Sir.
- Thanks.

01:21:51.945 --> 01:21:53.946
Where's Overwatch?

01:21:56.079 --> 01:21:58.211
<i>Overwatch, this is command.</i>

01:21:58.213 --> 01:22:00.678
When you get line of sight,
I need to know.

01:22:00.680 --> 01:22:01.878
Roger.

01:22:01.880 --> 01:22:04.348
- This is bad, Mike.
- It'll be fine, I promise.

01:22:09.079 --> 01:22:12.211
HAWTHORNE: <i>MacCauley,
you'have an old friend here.</i>

01:22:12.213 --> 01:22:14.947
<i>He wants to come aboard,
and he wants to talk.</i>

01:22:23.680 --> 01:22:25.181
Your tag is lit.

01:22:44.213 --> 01:22:45.944
REPORTER: <i>We are live
outside the town of Beacon,</i>

01:22:45.946 --> 01:22:48.177
<i>where a Hudson
North train has derailed.</i>

01:22:48.179 --> 01:22:50.280
<i>No reports
of any casualties yet.</i>

01:22:52.213 --> 01:22:53.345
Get back.

01:22:53.347 --> 01:22:54.878
Go, go, go. Move back.

01:22:54.880 --> 01:22:56.348
Go, go.

01:22:58.880 --> 01:23:00.880
We got sound
on Lieutenant Murphy.

01:23:05.213 --> 01:23:06.244
REPORTER: <i>According to
our source on the ground,</i>

01:23:06.246 --> 01:23:09.344
<i>an ex-NYPD officer
has taken over the train</i>

01:23:09.346 --> 01:23:11.814
<i>and is holding
the passengers hostage.</i>

01:23:16.813 --> 01:23:18.014
Hey, Mike,
how we doing in there?

01:23:19.213 --> 01:23:20.544
Listen, man,
you know how this goes.

01:23:20.546 --> 01:23:22.914
We don't work this out, SWAT's
gonna take the train by force.

01:23:25.945 --> 01:23:27.080
Come on, talk to me, buddy.

01:23:30.946 --> 01:23:32.211
Where's my family?

01:23:32.213 --> 01:23:33.478
You said police
were on their way.

01:23:33.480 --> 01:23:35.411
ALEX: <i>They were, man.
I don't know what happened.</i>

01:23:35.413 --> 01:23:38.010
Look, we're doing
the best we can.

01:23:38.012 --> 01:23:39.910
You don't know
what's going on, Murph.

01:23:39.912 --> 01:23:41.877
Then tell me, all right?

01:23:41.879 --> 01:23:44.813
Just open the door, let me in.
I'm unarmed. I'm alone.

01:23:52.779 --> 01:23:54.046
How many people
you got in there?

01:23:56.880 --> 01:23:58.743
Mike, I wanna help you.
You gotta help me out.

01:23:58.745 --> 01:24:01.277
If I don't produce results,
they're gonna pull me out.

01:24:01.279 --> 01:24:03.944
Now, how many
hostages do you have?

01:24:03.946 --> 01:24:05.811
We gotta do something.

01:24:05.813 --> 01:24:07.348
Yeah, but what?
What can we do?

01:24:08.780 --> 01:24:10.811
Fifteen, 20.

01:24:10.813 --> 01:24:13.444
All right, just let some go.
Whoever you want.

01:24:13.446 --> 01:24:15.146
How do I know they'll be safe?

01:24:16.812 --> 01:24:18.678
The hostages?

01:24:18.680 --> 01:24:21.311
There's someone
I need to protect.

01:24:21.313 --> 01:24:23.144
Look, if you're worried
about someone's safety,

01:24:23.146 --> 01:24:24.313
just send them out with me.

01:24:26.680 --> 01:24:28.678
Not yet.

01:24:28.680 --> 01:24:30.047
No...

01:24:32.779 --> 01:24:35.810
Seven years we were partners.
You always had my back.

01:24:35.812 --> 01:24:37.813
Let someone else
have yours for once.

01:24:41.212 --> 01:24:42.214
Mike.

01:24:44.147 --> 01:24:46.677
Look, I tell you what.
I'll make an exchange, okay?

01:24:46.679 --> 01:24:49.746
Release some hostages
and take me instead.

01:25:07.012 --> 01:25:08.046
SNIPER: They're coming out.

01:25:09.279 --> 01:25:12.045
ALEX: Come on out.
Come on out.

01:25:12.047 --> 01:25:13.410
OFFICER: Come on.
Come on. This way.

01:25:13.412 --> 01:25:15.678
ALEX: <i>Watch your step.
Go that way. Follow her.</i>

01:25:15.680 --> 01:25:16.978
All right, stay in line.

01:25:16.980 --> 01:25:20.211
REPORTER: <i>Yes, it does appear
that hostages are being released.</i>

01:25:20.213 --> 01:25:23.780
<i>It is unclear at this time
how many remain on the train.</i>

01:25:30.912 --> 01:25:33.181
- Is that it?
- Yeah. Come on.

01:25:36.845 --> 01:25:38.943
All right. Patrol's on
their way to your house.

01:25:38.945 --> 01:25:40.214
No sirens.

01:25:44.679 --> 01:25:46.110
(ALEX SIGHS)

01:25:46.112 --> 01:25:48.277
They have you tagged.

01:25:48.279 --> 01:25:50.444
This goes on much longer,
they're gonna board.

01:25:50.446 --> 01:25:52.181
They don't want a cop
caught in the crossfire.

01:25:53.346 --> 01:25:55.411
Come on, put the gun down.

01:25:55.413 --> 01:25:57.314
Jesus, I'm unarmed. Come on.

01:25:58.379 --> 01:25:59.780
(ALEX SIGHS)

01:26:05.746 --> 01:26:08.044
Tell them
to turn the lights off.

01:26:08.046 --> 01:26:10.047
ALEX: <i>Kill the lights.</i>

01:26:10.680 --> 01:26:11.714
Cut the lights.

01:26:15.446 --> 01:26:17.944
- Thanks, pal.
- Come on, you know the deal.

01:26:17.946 --> 01:26:20.144
We lost audio.

01:26:20.146 --> 01:26:22.877
You were right, there is
a witness on the train.

01:26:22.879 --> 01:26:25.111
They were supposed to meet
the FBI at Cold Spring.

01:26:25.113 --> 01:26:28.843
- FBI? Special Agent Garcia?
- You know?

01:26:28.845 --> 01:26:30.711
Hawthorne just pulled
jurisdiction from him.

01:26:30.713 --> 01:26:32.411
Hawthorne. That figures.

01:26:32.413 --> 01:26:35.677
I want eyes on.
Confirm visuals.

01:26:35.679 --> 01:26:36.777
(WHIRRING)

01:26:36.779 --> 01:26:39.177
SNIPER: <i>Friendly fire tag
is lit in blue.</i>

01:26:39.179 --> 01:26:40.443
<i>Visual confirmed.</i>

01:26:40.445 --> 01:26:42.777
Mike, what the hell happened?

01:26:42.779 --> 01:26:43.811
I talk to you,

01:26:43.813 --> 01:26:45.747
next thing I know
you're taking people hostage.

01:26:46.945 --> 01:26:48.743
They killed three passengers,
including a fed.

01:26:48.745 --> 01:26:50.678
They derailed the train.

01:26:50.680 --> 01:26:52.914
- All to get some evidence.
- Okay.

01:26:54.112 --> 01:26:55.277
So where is it, Mike?

01:26:55.279 --> 01:26:56.910
Not until Karen
and Danny are safe.

01:26:56.912 --> 01:26:59.045
ALEX: Local PD's
calling me directly.

01:26:59.047 --> 01:27:00.380
So, we wait.

01:27:03.179 --> 01:27:04.880
We wait.

01:27:06.046 --> 01:27:07.312
Yeah.

01:27:10.279 --> 01:27:11.711
How you guys doing?

01:27:11.713 --> 01:27:12.878
- EVA: Yeah, I'm good.
- JACKSON: Not too bad.

01:27:12.880 --> 01:27:15.614
- Oh, perfect.
- Fine, but I gotta pee.

01:27:18.079 --> 01:27:19.978
Mike, I know
this isn't you, man.

01:27:19.980 --> 01:27:25.077
Look, you say they set you up,
you got a witness, evidence.

01:27:25.079 --> 01:27:27.410
- I believe you, but...
- But what?

01:27:27.412 --> 01:27:29.145
It doesn't matter
what I believe.

01:27:29.147 --> 01:27:31.710
It's what I can prove.

01:27:31.712 --> 01:27:33.943
Look, you want confirmation
on your family. I understand.

01:27:33.945 --> 01:27:35.077
But from where I sit,

01:27:35.079 --> 01:27:36.410
I say we end
this thing right now.

01:27:36.412 --> 01:27:39.277
Just give me what you got,
nobody else has to get hurt.

01:27:39.279 --> 01:27:43.743
You telling me that
as a detective or a friend?

01:27:43.745 --> 01:27:45.843
I don't know, Mike.
What would you tell me?

01:27:45.845 --> 01:27:47.181
(SIGHS)

01:27:48.880 --> 01:27:50.947
We're running
out of time, man.

01:27:52.980 --> 01:27:55.978
Mike, I get it. You wanna
do the noble thing here.

01:27:55.980 --> 01:27:56.877
But I got news for you.

01:27:56.879 --> 01:27:58.146
There ain't
no such thing as noble.

01:28:07.946 --> 01:28:09.943
- It was you.
- What are you talking about?

01:28:09.945 --> 01:28:12.746
You called me. You knew
about the witness. You...

01:28:14.279 --> 01:28:15.744
You knew what they saw.

01:28:15.746 --> 01:28:17.843
Yeah, I told you
what happened.

01:28:17.845 --> 01:28:19.279
It was a cop who killed him.

01:28:20.813 --> 01:28:23.344
- You set me up.
- Hey, slow down, Mike.

01:28:23.346 --> 01:28:26.110
You killed Enrique Mendez.

01:28:26.112 --> 01:28:27.943
You knew Prynne was
getting on this train.

01:28:27.945 --> 01:28:30.011
- You targeted me.
- Mike...

01:28:30.013 --> 01:28:33.777
An ex-cop rides this train every day.
You knew.

01:28:33.779 --> 01:28:35.177
Mike, whoever's talking to you,
they're trying to get in your...

01:28:35.179 --> 01:28:36.309
Son of a...

01:28:36.311 --> 01:28:38.710
- (PEOPLE EXCLAIM)
- You've lost it, man.

01:28:38.712 --> 01:28:40.743
Talk, God damn it. Talk!

01:28:40.745 --> 01:28:42.010
SNIPER: <i>Friendly's
engaged with the target.</i>

01:28:42.012 --> 01:28:44.145
I repeat, friendly's
engaged with the target.

01:28:44.147 --> 01:28:46.744
Do not fire
until you get a clear shot.

01:28:46.746 --> 01:28:48.377
And say what?

01:28:48.379 --> 01:28:51.077
That you killed
three people, a fed?

01:28:51.079 --> 01:28:53.310
You derailed a train and took
the passengers hostage,

01:28:53.312 --> 01:28:56.343
all 'cause some mystery woman
threatened your family?

01:28:56.345 --> 01:28:57.910
You did this.

01:28:57.912 --> 01:28:59.777
Doesn't look
that way, does it?

01:28:59.779 --> 01:29:02.110
So why don't you
put down the gun

01:29:02.112 --> 01:29:04.077
before someone
you love gets hurt?

01:29:04.079 --> 01:29:06.713
Where are they?
Where's my family?

01:29:08.712 --> 01:29:09.843
(GUN COCKS)

01:29:09.845 --> 01:29:11.978
I will kill you, Murph.
I swear to God.

01:29:11.980 --> 01:29:15.176
Okay, okay, okay.
I'm trying to help you here.

01:29:15.178 --> 01:29:17.077
A lot of powerful people
have got a lot to lose

01:29:17.079 --> 01:29:18.410
if that evidence gets out.

01:29:18.412 --> 01:29:21.344
They have eyes everywhere,
even inside the Bureau.

01:29:21.346 --> 01:29:23.244
I told them to put the
witness on your train.

01:29:23.246 --> 01:29:24.410
I thought I was
doing you a favor.

01:29:24.412 --> 01:29:25.577
You needed the money.

01:29:25.579 --> 01:29:28.410
But you couldn't just do
what she asked, could you?

01:29:28.412 --> 01:29:30.680
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

01:29:31.445 --> 01:29:33.778
(BREATHES HEAVILY)

01:29:33.780 --> 01:29:36.814
If I don't answer that,
your family dies.

01:29:39.112 --> 01:29:40.646
So why don't you
give me the gun?

01:29:42.046 --> 01:29:43.814
You got no choice, Mike.

01:29:46.446 --> 01:29:48.143
It doesn't have to
end this way.

01:29:48.145 --> 01:29:49.777
(CONTINUES RINGING)

01:29:49.779 --> 01:29:52.110
Come on. Karen, Danny...

01:29:52.112 --> 01:29:53.779
Don't you dare
say their names.

01:29:54.446 --> 01:29:57.110
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

01:29:57.112 --> 01:29:59.177
You've done enough, Mike.

01:29:59.179 --> 01:30:01.347
(CONTINUES RINGING)

01:30:07.979 --> 01:30:09.677
- JOANNA: <i>Is it done?</i>
- We're good.

01:30:09.679 --> 01:30:10.680
<i>You know what to do.</i>

01:30:15.212 --> 01:30:20.110
See, the thing is, Mike...
I got a family, too, you know.

01:30:20.112 --> 01:30:21.913
- All right, who's Prynne?
- (ALL CLAMORING)

01:30:24.779 --> 01:30:26.011
MICHAEL: Murph, listen to me.

01:30:26.013 --> 01:30:27.245
All I gotta do
is call her back, Mike.

01:30:32.178 --> 01:30:34.014
Come on.

01:30:38.179 --> 01:30:40.080
All right, who's Prynne?

01:30:43.179 --> 01:30:44.880
Who's Prynne?

01:30:47.445 --> 01:30:50.047
Mike, who's Prynne?

01:30:53.745 --> 01:30:55.245
Who's Prynne?

01:30:59.311 --> 01:31:01.613
